October 14. Calendar 21.
People v. Roosevelt Davis.

31
00:03:08,137 --> 00:03:11,436
Docket number 8483, September 19.

32
00:03:11,808 --> 00:03:14,368
Defendant is charged
with attempted grand larceny.

33
00:03:14,444 --> 00:03:17,572
Does the defendant waive
the reading of the rights and charges?

34
00:03:17,647 --> 00:03:18,545
We do.

35
00:03:18,615 --> 00:03:22,016
For the People, Saul Kreiglitz.
For the defendant, Aaron Levinsky.

36
00:03:24,454 --> 00:03:27,048
- What are you gonna give me on him?
- A misdemeanor.

37
00:03:27,123 --> 00:03:28,886
He's an accomplice. Disorderly conduct?

38
00:03:28,958 --> 00:03:30,585
Come on, he shows a prior.

39
00:03:30,660 --> 00:03:33,595
Yeah, he shows a prior,
but he hasn't done any hard time.

40
00:03:33,663 --> 00:03:34,755
Give him a break.

41
00:03:34,831 --> 00:03:37,061
What are we supposed to do,
give him a medal?

42
00:03:37,767 --> 00:03:40,429
- How much you talking about?
- We're talking $100.

43
00:03:40,837 --> 00:03:41,804
$50.

44
00:03:42,438 --> 00:03:43,996
$75. Best I can do.

45
00:03:45,708 --> 00:03:47,369
Hey, hey, coming through here.

46
00:03:51,381 --> 00:03:54,646
Excuse me. Coming through.

47
00:03:55,051 --> 00:03:56,541
...twenty-five years.

48
00:03:56,619 --> 00:04:00,248
She started to laugh and told me
to go to hell, and ordered me to leave.

49
00:04:03,126 --> 00:04:04,787
- Rose?
- In a minute.

50
00:04:09,966 --> 00:04:13,561
Gonzales, your lawyer has just entered
a plea of guilty on your behalf.

51
00:04:14,704 --> 00:04:17,298
You understand, pleading guilty,
you waive your right...

52
00:04:17,373 --> 00:04:18,670
There she is, Arthur.

53
00:04:18,741 --> 00:04:20,606
Now, is that what you wish to do?

54
00:04:22,979 --> 00:04:25,470
- Do you understand what I've said?
- Sit down, Rose.

55
00:04:25,548 --> 00:04:27,982
- Is that what you wish to do?
- Yes, yes, it is.

56
00:04:28,818 --> 00:04:31,719
By this plea of guilty,
you're giving up important rights...

57
00:04:31,788 --> 00:04:34,814
...I wish to make you aware of.
- She looks terrible.

58
00:04:34,958 --> 00:04:37,722
Remember, Clarence said
this would be the worst of it.

59
00:04:37,927 --> 00:04:39,053
Yes.

60
00:04:39,729 --> 00:04:43,256
Do you understand that by pleading guilty,
you're waiving your right...

61
00:04:43,333 --> 00:04:47,133
...to confront and cross-examine
any witnesses against you?

62
00:04:48,037 --> 00:04:51,268
And you are also giving up
your right to remain silent?

63
00:04:51,708 --> 00:04:55,906
Be calm, Rose. Everything's under control.
We'll be out of here in no time.

64
00:04:58,147 --> 00:05:01,082
Now, sir, did you take property
from premises...

65
00:05:01,150 --> 00:05:04,950
...at 540 East 8th Street
without permission of authority?

66
00:05:05,021 --> 00:05:07,216
Are you pleading guilty? Because you are...

67
00:05:07,290 --> 00:05:11,920
Did you see who's here, at $250 an hour?
Clarence fucking Middleton.

68
00:05:11,995 --> 00:05:13,553
Last I heard, it was $350.

69
00:05:13,629 --> 00:05:15,961
- Who's the client?
- I don't know.

70
00:05:16,032 --> 00:05:17,226
Say it aloud.

71
00:05:18,334 --> 00:05:19,301
Guilty.

72
00:05:19,369 --> 00:05:23,396
Did anybody make any threats or promises
in order to induce you to plead guilty?

73
00:05:23,806 --> 00:05:26,798
Saul, do you have the Kirk folder?
I'll be taking that one.

74
00:05:27,010 --> 00:05:29,205
Mr. Gonzales,
this is your third appearance...

75
00:05:29,278 --> 00:05:30,267
Thank you.

76
00:05:30,346 --> 00:05:34,180
...before this court since last year.
The sentence of this court is six months.

77
00:05:34,550 --> 00:05:36,848
Do you understand what I've said so far?

78
00:05:40,890 --> 00:05:42,323
What have you done?

79
00:05:42,759 --> 00:05:45,421
Counsel. Notify your client
of his right to appeal.

80
00:05:45,495 --> 00:05:47,725
Thank you, Mr. Torres. Next case.

81
00:05:48,031 --> 00:05:52,798
Calendar 28. People v. Claudia Kirk.
Docket 6418.

82
00:05:53,102 --> 00:05:56,265
The defendant is charged
with manslaughter in the first degree.

83
00:05:56,339 --> 00:06:00,139
- The Morales case is next on the docket.
- All in good time, Mr. Levinsky.

84
00:06:00,243 --> 00:06:04,202
- I have an appointment in Part 30.
- It'll wait. Sit down, please. Let's move it.

85
00:06:04,280 --> 00:06:05,269
Take it easy.

86
00:06:05,348 --> 00:06:07,407
- My name's wrong.
- We'll take care of it.

87
00:06:07,550 --> 00:06:09,780
Counsel, state your appearances
for the record.

88
00:06:09,852 --> 00:06:12,286
Francis Xavier MacMillan
for the prosecution.

89
00:06:12,355 --> 00:06:14,346
Clarence Middleton for the defendant.

90
00:06:14,457 --> 00:06:17,620
The defendant has been indicted
in the county of New York...

91
00:06:17,693 --> 00:06:20,025
...for first-degree manslaughter.
We request...

92
00:06:20,096 --> 00:06:21,154
May I say something?

93
00:06:21,230 --> 00:06:25,189
...she be given psychiatric evaluation
to determine her capacity to stand trial.

94
00:06:25,268 --> 00:06:27,736
In accordance with article 730 of the CPL...

95
00:06:27,837 --> 00:06:31,637
...she was remanded to the New York
County Prison Hospital for examination.

96
00:06:31,707 --> 00:06:32,765
Excuse me!

97
00:06:32,842 --> 00:06:36,437
The psychiatrists' report finds
the defendant not competent to stand trial.

98
00:06:36,512 --> 00:06:38,104
I have something to say!

99
00:06:38,181 --> 00:06:42,015
They recommend that she be committed
to a mental facility and the People concur.

100
00:06:42,852 --> 00:06:44,945
- Hands by your side.
- All right.

101
00:06:45,021 --> 00:06:47,046
I can't hear. I have a right to hear.

102
00:06:47,123 --> 00:06:50,354
Defendant will keep quiet
if she knows what's good for her.

103
00:06:51,794 --> 00:06:54,228
- Clarence, have you read these reports?
- We have.

104
00:06:54,297 --> 00:06:55,924
- Do you move to confirm?
- I do.

105
00:06:55,998 --> 00:07:00,697
- Consult with your client.
- Larry, in view of the overriding fact...

106
00:07:00,770 --> 00:07:04,672
- Could you please let me go?
- The fact is, she's impossible to talk to.

107
00:07:05,575 --> 00:07:07,941
Clarence, please consult with your client.

108
00:07:08,744 --> 00:07:10,336
Make it quick!

109
00:07:11,114 --> 00:07:12,945
- Get your hands off me!
- Face forward.

110
00:07:16,752 --> 00:07:17,776
Claudia...

111
00:07:17,854 --> 00:07:22,154
Listen, they don't have my name right.
I don't want to be known as Kirk.

112
00:07:22,225 --> 00:07:24,693
Do you understand?
My name is Draper. Claudia Draper.

113
00:07:24,760 --> 00:07:25,749
Yes.

114
00:07:25,828 --> 00:07:28,058
- D-R-A-P-E-R.
- Yes, we'll get that changed.

115
00:07:28,131 --> 00:07:28,859
Good.

116
00:07:28,931 --> 00:07:32,389
Now look, Claudia, I am trying to help you.
We all are.

117
00:07:32,635 --> 00:07:33,863
What's going on here?

118
00:07:33,936 --> 00:07:36,928
We're trying to do
what we feel is best for you.

119
00:07:38,407 --> 00:07:39,772
Who is "we"?

120
00:07:39,842 --> 00:07:42,333
We offered you
criminally negligent homicide.

121
00:07:42,411 --> 00:07:43,935
You didn't want us to.

122
00:07:44,514 --> 00:07:45,572
Hey.

123
00:07:47,216 --> 00:07:48,581
Who are you?

124
00:07:49,719 --> 00:07:50,651
What?

125
00:07:51,320 --> 00:07:52,480
Who are you?

126
00:07:53,856 --> 00:07:57,587
Well, Clarence Middleton.
Don't you remember me?

127
00:07:58,661 --> 00:08:00,128
Who do you work for?

128
00:08:01,330 --> 00:08:04,993
- I'm your lawyer, Claudia.
- Good. We're on the right track.

129
00:08:05,134 --> 00:08:09,161
We have to claim
that you're incompetent to stand trial.

130
00:08:10,006 --> 00:08:13,635
- Do you understand?
- No, I didn't give you permission to do that.

131
00:08:13,709 --> 00:08:15,802
- I'm not incompetent.
- Of course you're not.

132
00:08:15,878 --> 00:08:18,870
- I'm innocent.
- I know you are. But that's not the issue.

133
00:08:18,948 --> 00:08:22,111
- What do you mean it's not the issue?
- The doctors agreed.

134
00:08:22,185 --> 00:08:26,246
Your parents agree it's best if you're
in a hospital rather than in a prison.

135
00:08:26,322 --> 00:08:28,290
I don't give a shit what they say!

136
00:08:28,357 --> 00:08:30,882
Your parents love you.
It's all been arranged.

137
00:08:30,960 --> 00:08:34,191
- You goddamn son of a bitch!
- Arthur, stop her!

138
00:08:34,263 --> 00:08:37,289
I'm not incompetent.
I'm not incompetent, you are!

139
00:08:37,366 --> 00:08:39,698
Get her off me! Get her off me!

140
00:08:39,769 --> 00:08:41,828
- Move it now.
- Hit him again.

141
00:08:41,938 --> 00:08:43,496
Quiet in the court!

142
00:08:43,606 --> 00:08:44,937
You can't lock me up.

143
00:08:45,007 --> 00:08:46,804
Let go of me! Get away from me!

144
00:08:46,876 --> 00:08:48,867
Let me through. That's my daughter.

145
00:08:48,945 --> 00:08:50,606
- Calm down.
- Don't hurt her.

146
00:08:50,680 --> 00:08:52,272
Sir, restrain yourself.

147
00:08:52,348 --> 00:08:54,407
Why are you trying to put me away?

148
00:08:54,917 --> 00:08:56,817
Why are you trying to lock me up?

149
00:08:57,053 --> 00:08:58,611
You are all in cahoots.

150
00:08:58,888 --> 00:09:01,049
Put me down!
There's nothing wrong with me!

151
00:09:01,490 --> 00:09:03,390
God! Keep going!

152
00:09:03,826 --> 00:09:05,589
- No!
- Watch out!

153
00:09:05,661 --> 00:09:07,822
Put me down. I need a lawyer!

154
00:09:08,497 --> 00:09:11,295
- Quiet in the court!
- All right, everybody settle down.

155
00:09:11,367 --> 00:09:12,766
Order in the court!

156
00:09:14,503 --> 00:09:16,903
Order in the court.
It's over, folks. Sit down.

157
00:09:16,973 --> 00:09:20,465
- God, Clarence, are you all right?
- I'm bleeding. My glasses...

158
00:09:20,543 --> 00:09:21,737
Can we go on?

159
00:09:22,078 --> 00:09:25,809
No, we can't go on. I've been attacked
in a courtroom, for Christ's sake.

160
00:09:26,115 --> 00:09:29,141
I hereby request permission
to be released from this case.

161
00:09:29,218 --> 00:09:33,245
- Can't you just move to confirm?
- No, sir! Get someone from Legal Aid.

162
00:09:33,322 --> 00:09:34,846
I'm going to a doctor.

163
00:09:37,593 --> 00:09:39,754
- Are you all right?
- I need a Legal Aid member.

164
00:09:41,297 --> 00:09:43,094
Where's Torbick? Where's Morella?

165
00:09:43,165 --> 00:09:45,565
Don't we have anybody
in the appointments list?

166
00:09:45,635 --> 00:09:46,693
Levinsky.

167
00:09:47,637 --> 00:09:49,070
Where are you going?

168
00:09:50,273 --> 00:09:53,299
To get Morella. I have an appearance
in Part 30, Your Honor.

169
00:09:53,376 --> 00:09:56,868
- Let me get Morella. He's on catch.
- But I caught you.

170
00:09:58,381 --> 00:10:01,282
Your Honor, I respectfully submit
that my caseload is...

171
00:10:01,350 --> 00:10:05,286
Mr. Levinsky, is your caseload too heavy
to accept any appointments in this court?

172
00:10:08,024 --> 00:10:10,549
For the record, Mr. Middleton withdraws.

173
00:10:10,660 --> 00:10:13,754
Mr. Levinsky is appointed counsel
for the defense.

174
00:10:13,829 --> 00:10:16,024
It's 7:30. We have two psychiatric reports.

175
00:10:16,265 --> 00:10:18,631
All it takes from you
is a motion to confirm.

176
00:10:19,135 --> 00:10:22,332
- I haven't seen the reports.
- See them. Let's move it.

177
00:10:22,705 --> 00:10:24,400
Let's get this one out of here.

178
00:10:27,543 --> 00:10:29,636
- What's the original charge?
- Manslaughter.

179
00:10:29,712 --> 00:10:31,339
The original charge is not the issue.

180
00:10:31,414 --> 00:10:35,783
Psychiatrists' reports say she's unfit
to stand trial. Let's have your motion.

181
00:10:37,753 --> 00:10:40,244
Didn't you say you were in a hurry,
Mr. Levinsky?

182
00:10:41,057 --> 00:10:43,525
- I am in a hurry.
- Then let's have your motion.

183
00:10:43,592 --> 00:10:45,082
I don't have all day.

184
00:10:53,903 --> 00:10:55,393
I move to controvert.

185
00:10:57,206 --> 00:10:59,538
For the record,
the defense moves to challenge.

186
00:11:02,545 --> 00:11:04,035
You wanted a motion.

187
00:11:04,914 --> 00:11:06,313
That's my motion.

188
00:11:12,254 --> 00:11:14,051
What's your basis, Levinsky?

189
00:11:15,024 --> 00:11:18,323
Well, as I observed,
the defendant seemed a bit reluctant.

190
00:11:18,394 --> 00:11:20,385
I have to consult with my client.

191
00:11:24,834 --> 00:11:28,270
Fine. Adjourn until Monday.

192
00:11:28,637 --> 00:11:30,662
Monday? I haven't even met the woman.

193
00:11:30,940 --> 00:11:33,534
Between now and Monday
I have no time to prepare a case.

194
00:11:33,609 --> 00:11:37,067
Adjourn until Monday, Part 65. Next case.

195
00:11:45,554 --> 00:11:49,012
Calendar 29, People v. Calvin Johnson.

196
00:11:49,258 --> 00:11:52,523
Docket 6914, robbery in the first degree.

197
00:11:55,231 --> 00:11:57,597
Aaron? Are you out of your mind?

198
00:11:57,666 --> 00:12:01,568
- I don't have to take that shit from him.
- Of course you do, he's the judge.

199
00:12:02,238 --> 00:12:05,366
Look, do yourself a favor.
Go back in and settle up.

200
00:12:09,545 --> 00:12:13,675
- Did you see that girl work over Middleton?
- I wish she'd nailed MacMillan, too.

201
00:12:13,816 --> 00:12:17,445
Pardon me, I'd like talk to you.
I'm Arthur Kirk, the girl's father.

202
00:12:17,520 --> 00:12:19,283
I'd like to talk to you, too.

203
00:12:19,355 --> 00:12:21,323
- Aaron? See you later?
- Yeah, yeah.

204
00:12:21,390 --> 00:12:22,652
My wife, Rose.

205
00:12:24,727 --> 00:12:26,251
- Mrs. Kirk.
- How do you do?

206
00:12:26,328 --> 00:12:28,956
I'm still shaking.
I can't believe what happened.

207
00:12:29,064 --> 00:12:30,827
- Sit down.
- Yeah, thank you.

208
00:12:30,900 --> 00:12:33,835
Tell me, why did you stop the motion?

209
00:12:34,303 --> 00:12:35,998
I'm not familiar with the case yet.

210
00:12:36,071 --> 00:12:39,768
The case is about a very disturbed girl.
She needs to be hospitalized.

211
00:12:39,842 --> 00:12:43,710
I haven't read the reports,
and I have to confer with the defendant.

212
00:12:43,779 --> 00:12:47,237
- How can you confer? She's sick.
- I know how painful this is for you.

213
00:12:47,316 --> 00:12:49,841
You're damn right. What about her pain?

214
00:12:50,219 --> 00:12:52,915
- Arthur.
- You see, we're talking about my child.

215
00:12:53,189 --> 00:12:56,625
She needs to be in a hospital,
not some kind of a prison cell.

216
00:12:57,193 --> 00:12:58,660
And let me tell you.

217
00:12:58,994 --> 00:13:03,454
- She is in no condition to stand trial.
- Darling, he didn't say he wouldn't do it.

218
00:13:07,136 --> 00:13:10,333
Of course. You didn't say that, did you?
Please, forgive me.

219
00:13:11,440 --> 00:13:15,536
- I guess I'm not handling this too well.
- That's perfectly understandable, sir.

220
00:13:15,611 --> 00:13:18,580
- Will you be seeing her soon?
- I'll have to, yes.

221
00:13:19,181 --> 00:13:21,649
- Will you tell her that I love her?
- Of course.

222
00:13:21,717 --> 00:13:22,684
Please.

223
00:13:22,885 --> 00:13:24,375
I want to give you my card.

224
00:13:24,820 --> 00:13:27,880
If you need anything, anything at all,
just call my office.

225
00:13:27,990 --> 00:13:29,082
Thank you.

226
00:13:29,158 --> 00:13:30,785
- Mrs. Kirk?
- Good-bye.

227
00:13:45,007 --> 00:13:47,202
Doctor Arantes to the conference room.

228
00:13:47,643 --> 00:13:49,668
Doctor Arantes to the conference room.

229
00:13:49,845 --> 00:13:51,540
I'm here to see Claudia Draper.

230
00:13:53,249 --> 00:13:54,716
Levinsky, Legal Aid.

231
00:13:58,320 --> 00:13:59,981
May I inspect your bag, sir?

232
00:14:10,833 --> 00:14:12,266
Your name tag, sir.

233
00:14:14,670 --> 00:14:18,834
Dr. Simon, 817. Dr. Simon, Psychiatry, 817.

234
00:14:18,908 --> 00:14:20,034
Come with me, sir.

235
00:14:22,311 --> 00:14:24,711
- Good night, John.
- Good night, Dr. Morrison.

236
00:14:26,916 --> 00:14:29,407
- Excuse me. Dr. Morrison?
- Yes?

237
00:14:30,553 --> 00:14:34,114
My name is Aaron Levinsky.
I'm the new attorney for Claudia Draper.

238
00:14:34,189 --> 00:14:37,681
I just read the report
that you did with Dr. Arantes about her.

239
00:14:38,127 --> 00:14:40,789
- Is there going to be a hearing?
- I think so, yeah.

240
00:14:40,863 --> 00:14:42,387
Yeah, you got a minute?

241
00:14:42,598 --> 00:14:45,658
Not about Mrs. Draper.
It wouldn't be ethical. Sorry.

242
00:14:45,734 --> 00:14:50,671
I'm just curious about a couple of things
you wrote here in this report.

243
00:14:50,806 --> 00:14:54,401
You mention that you found her
flagrantly sexual...

244
00:14:55,044 --> 00:14:58,980
...and had random visions
and was subject to paranoid...

245
00:14:59,048 --> 00:15:00,948
I'm really sorry, Mr. Levinsky.

246
00:15:03,052 --> 00:15:04,041
Doctor?

247
00:15:05,220 --> 00:15:08,121
Doctor?
I just want to ask you one question.

248
00:15:09,191 --> 00:15:10,385
Is she crazy?

249
00:15:12,361 --> 00:15:14,056
Crazy is a word I dislike.

250
00:15:14,763 --> 00:15:17,254
Dr. Hodges, telephone on line 3.

251
00:15:17,533 --> 00:15:19,728
Do I think she should go to prison? No.

252
00:15:20,369 --> 00:15:23,827
She's where she belongs, Mr. Levinsky.
Good night.

253
00:15:25,140 --> 00:15:26,334
Good night.

254
00:15:54,069 --> 00:15:55,502
Shut up, Mary!

255
00:16:10,753 --> 00:16:12,983
Watch out for Babby.
She might try something.

256
00:16:13,055 --> 00:16:15,387
Dr. Morrison's left a prescription for her.

257
00:16:22,464 --> 00:16:24,159
You can wait in here, sir.

258
00:16:36,712 --> 00:16:37,974
Claudia...

259
00:16:38,814 --> 00:16:42,250
...you feel more better.
You feel more calm, huh?

260
00:16:43,819 --> 00:16:45,787
You are a woman of passion.

261
00:16:46,655 --> 00:16:50,113
Passion is good in the bed, but not here.

262
00:16:54,530 --> 00:16:57,158
Someone is waiting to see you.

263
00:16:58,534 --> 00:16:59,523
What?

264
00:16:59,802 --> 00:17:01,861
Someone is here to see you.

265
00:17:12,614 --> 00:17:13,945
She's fine.

266
00:17:16,552 --> 00:17:19,885
- Do you want some help, Dr. Arantes?
- No, no.

267
00:17:20,456 --> 00:17:21,889
You just follow me.

268
00:17:23,358 --> 00:17:26,987
Follow me, Claudia. Just follow me.

269
00:17:29,531 --> 00:17:32,989
- Right this way, Mrs. Draper.
- Thank you, Manuel.

270
00:17:44,413 --> 00:17:45,880
You must be Claudia.

271
00:17:46,582 --> 00:17:48,914
And I hope you're Mr. Green from Chicago.

272
00:17:49,885 --> 00:17:52,115
Just call me Allen. Sit down.

273
00:17:52,588 --> 00:17:53,680
Thank you.

274
00:17:54,656 --> 00:17:56,920
- Champagne?
- Yes, please.

275
00:18:17,813 --> 00:18:19,974
I've never had to take a test before.

276
00:18:20,783 --> 00:18:22,774
Not since high school.

277
00:18:27,856 --> 00:18:30,416
Do you have certain questions
that you ask?

278
00:18:31,393 --> 00:18:32,758
Things like that?

279
00:18:33,128 --> 00:18:34,117
No.

280
00:18:34,863 --> 00:18:36,956
I just go by the seat of my pants.

281
00:18:39,601 --> 00:18:40,863
How am I doing?

282
00:18:42,471 --> 00:18:44,462
I'm about to slide over my chair.

283
00:18:56,418 --> 00:18:59,444
Hello, Mrs. Draper.
My name is Aaron Levinsky.

284
00:19:00,956 --> 00:19:02,981
I'm an attorney sent by the court.

285
00:19:04,293 --> 00:19:06,693
Mr. Middleton
doesn't represent you anymore.

286
00:19:14,503 --> 00:19:16,596
Would you like to discuss your case?

287
00:19:22,411 --> 00:19:24,675
I don't know if you can follow any of this...

288
00:19:24,746 --> 00:19:28,079
...but do you understand
that I'm gonna go to court on your behalf?

289
00:19:34,957 --> 00:19:37,755
And tonight I got to go home to Brooklyn
on the subway...

290
00:19:37,860 --> 00:19:39,919
...and that scares the shit out of me.

291
00:19:41,330 --> 00:19:43,491
I'm real tired. It's been a long day.

292
00:19:44,900 --> 00:19:46,390
You're breaking my heart.

293
00:19:47,236 --> 00:19:49,534
- Terrific. She can talk.
- Talk?

294
00:19:50,772 --> 00:19:53,707
I can dance, juggle, card tricks.

295
00:19:57,446 --> 00:20:00,040
What kind of a show
do I have to put on for you?

296
00:20:00,916 --> 00:20:02,440
Did I say something wrong?

297
00:20:04,186 --> 00:20:08,748
It seems I can't get a fair trial
unless I put on a good show for...

298
00:20:10,592 --> 00:20:11,718
...who now?

299
00:20:12,928 --> 00:20:16,125
Aaron Levinsky, Legal Aid.

300
00:20:16,198 --> 00:20:18,063
- No, it's not like that.
- No?

301
00:20:19,101 --> 00:20:21,001
Well, how do I get to stand trial?

302
00:20:21,236 --> 00:20:22,362
You don't have...

303
00:20:22,437 --> 00:20:25,463
How do I get to stand trial?
That's what I want to know!

304
00:20:27,609 --> 00:20:30,703
That's okay. Close the door, please.
I'm her attorney.

305
00:20:31,513 --> 00:20:33,845
- Says who?
- Says the court.

306
00:20:34,349 --> 00:20:36,374
If you need me, I'll be right out here.

307
00:20:39,388 --> 00:20:41,049
You think I'm gonna need him?

308
00:20:42,190 --> 00:20:45,853
Well, haven't you heard?
I lash out and strike people at random.

309
00:20:47,029 --> 00:20:48,929
I know. I was there.

310
00:20:50,966 --> 00:20:54,800
- I think you broke his nose.
- So the day's not a total loss.

311
00:20:58,073 --> 00:21:00,906
All right, what we've got here
is a 730 process.

312
00:21:02,044 --> 00:21:04,877
This is a process
whereby the State is assuming that you...

313
00:21:04,947 --> 00:21:06,744
- Are you married?
- Pardon me?

314
00:21:08,550 --> 00:21:09,915
You got a missus?

315
00:21:12,854 --> 00:21:14,287
She give good head?

316
00:21:16,158 --> 00:21:18,922
You want to talk
about your situation here or what?

317
00:21:20,195 --> 00:21:22,686
You've been indicted
for manslaughter first degree.

318
00:21:22,798 --> 00:21:24,129
I know all that.

319
00:21:25,133 --> 00:21:26,760
Tell me why you're here.

320
00:21:29,504 --> 00:21:32,200
- The truth?
- No, the bullshit, Levinsky.

321
00:21:33,141 --> 00:21:36,907
I love listening to bullshit,
especially when I'm drowning in it.

322
00:21:38,647 --> 00:21:40,012
I know why you're here.

323
00:21:40,415 --> 00:21:42,849
- You're here to see if I'm crazy, right?
- No.

324
00:21:42,985 --> 00:21:45,818
No. No, you're here to see
just how crazy I am.

325
00:21:48,090 --> 00:21:51,253
Well, two psychiatrists already say
that you are incompetent.

326
00:21:51,526 --> 00:21:54,825
Morrison and Arantes? Frick and Frack?

327
00:21:56,598 --> 00:21:59,226
Arantes can barely speak English,
and Morrison...

328
00:22:00,302 --> 00:22:01,963
...he's a very weird guy.

329
00:22:02,604 --> 00:22:05,004
You know, I flashed,
and he didn't even look.

330
00:22:07,576 --> 00:22:09,476
How about you, Levinsky?

331
00:22:10,612 --> 00:22:12,045
Are you weird, too?

332
00:22:14,883 --> 00:22:16,714
I must be okay, I'm looking.

333
00:22:18,720 --> 00:22:21,621
- Your mother says she loves you.
- Fuck my mother!

334
00:22:22,924 --> 00:22:24,892
Why didn't you tell me you work for them?

335
00:22:24,960 --> 00:22:26,018
I'm not working for them...

336
00:22:26,094 --> 00:22:28,460
- Why didn't you tell me that?
- Hold it! Listen!

337
00:22:28,530 --> 00:22:32,398
- I came here to do my job in good faith.
- You talked to my mother?

338
00:22:32,467 --> 00:22:35,630
- Will you listen to me? You got a choice.
- What did she tell you?

339
00:22:35,704 --> 00:22:38,571
You can either cooperate with me
and maybe it goes your way...

340
00:22:38,640 --> 00:22:42,337
...or you can yell at me, I'll sign that
motion to commit, and that's it.

341
00:22:42,411 --> 00:22:44,003
You creep lawyers are all alike.

342
00:22:44,079 --> 00:22:47,344
As long as you get paid, you don't care
who goes where for how long.

343
00:22:47,416 --> 00:22:48,747
I'm not taking money from you.

344
00:22:48,817 --> 00:22:51,547
This one comes in here
and tells me if I don't kiss ass...

345
00:22:51,620 --> 00:22:53,315
...he's gonna walk out on me? Walk.

346
00:22:53,388 --> 00:22:56,050
And be held in contempt of court?
No, thank you.

347
00:22:56,224 --> 00:22:59,284
It doesn't work that way.
I'm stuck with you.

348
00:23:01,663 --> 00:23:03,255
Oh, man!

349
00:23:04,633 --> 00:23:05,463
Oh, boy.

350
00:23:08,737 --> 00:23:12,673
First, we have to get a shrink
to look at you and then you...

351
00:23:14,376 --> 00:23:15,707
No more shrinks.

352
00:23:17,045 --> 00:23:19,240
I'm giving you very good legal advice.

353
00:23:19,347 --> 00:23:23,181
Thanks. What I said about lawyers
goes double for shrinks.

354
00:23:24,986 --> 00:23:29,446
Mrs. Draper, there are two psychiatrists
who already say that you're crazy.

355
00:23:30,058 --> 00:23:33,494
You got to have at least one psychiatrist
who says you're not crazy...

356
00:23:33,562 --> 00:23:36,429
...or you don't have a case.
- Sure, I do. I'm my case.

357
00:23:37,032 --> 00:23:39,694
I get up there, I say my piece,
I prove I'm competent!

358
00:23:39,768 --> 00:23:43,260
Look, I don't know if you believe this,
but I'm a perfectly sane woman.

359
00:23:43,338 --> 00:23:47,069
And I don't bother anyone
who doesn't bother me first. You get it?

360
00:23:47,142 --> 00:23:49,872
I don't want any more quacks
running around in my head...

361
00:23:49,945 --> 00:23:51,913
...talking about my toilet training.

362
00:23:52,848 --> 00:23:57,649
There's only one thing that scares me.
A stupid client. And you terrify me.

363
00:23:58,587 --> 00:24:00,555
- Have you ever testified in court?
- No.

364
00:24:00,622 --> 00:24:02,783
- So you've never been cross-examined?
- No.

365
00:24:03,258 --> 00:24:05,726
- How long have you been hooking?
- Three years.

366
00:24:05,894 --> 00:24:10,228
- And you've never been busted?
- Never. Now tell me I'm incompetent.

367
00:24:15,036 --> 00:24:16,230
Well, look.

368
00:24:18,140 --> 00:24:21,871
Mrs. Draper, it doesn't look good
to beat up one of the city's top attorneys.

369
00:24:21,943 --> 00:24:24,776
Well, it may not have looked good,
but it sure felt good.

370
00:24:24,846 --> 00:24:29,249
What was I supposed to do,
sit there while my own lawyer says...

371
00:24:29,317 --> 00:24:31,251
...I’m incompetent to stand trial?

372
00:24:31,353 --> 00:24:32,183
Are you?

373
00:24:32,254 --> 00:24:34,916
How competent do you have to be,
for Christ's sake?

374
00:24:35,390 --> 00:24:36,652
Good point.

375
00:24:37,792 --> 00:24:40,727
Let's say for now
that you're not entirely incompetent.

376
00:24:40,795 --> 00:24:42,126
Yeah, let's say that.

377
00:24:42,197 --> 00:24:44,688
Let's say for now
that the doctors here are all wrong.

378
00:24:44,766 --> 00:24:48,031
- Yeah, let's say that, too.
- Then why is all this happening to you?

379
00:25:00,015 --> 00:25:01,209
Mrs. Draper?

380
00:25:06,755 --> 00:25:09,588
Do you want me to represent you
in this competency hearing?

381
00:25:12,894 --> 00:25:17,160
- I don't know. Are you any good?
- You had good. Now you got me.

382
00:25:20,635 --> 00:25:22,000
I could do worse.

383
00:25:22,938 --> 00:25:24,132
Don't be so sure.

384
00:25:25,273 --> 00:25:27,434
If we win at the hearing, you get a trial.

385
00:25:27,509 --> 00:25:30,569
But if you lose the trial,
you can go to jail for 25 years.

386
00:25:31,746 --> 00:25:36,308
I'll take the risk. Because if I don't,
I could end up wearing this bathrobe...

387
00:25:36,384 --> 00:25:38,284
...until I collect social security.

388
00:25:41,823 --> 00:25:44,087
MacMillan's gonna eat me alive.

389
00:25:46,027 --> 00:25:48,962
- All right, let's start at the beginning.
- Fine.

390
00:25:50,865 --> 00:25:53,698
- Give me some background details.
- All right.

391
00:25:56,371 --> 00:25:59,204
Now, you talk to me
and pretend I'm sane, okay?

392
00:26:00,976 --> 00:26:01,965
Okay.

393
00:26:02,577 --> 00:26:04,374
And I'll do the same for you.

394
00:26:05,747 --> 00:26:06,736
Okay?

395
00:26:08,283 --> 00:26:09,375
Thank you.

396
00:26:15,523 --> 00:26:16,512
Frank.

397
00:26:17,492 --> 00:26:18,584
MacMillan.

398
00:26:19,060 --> 00:26:20,550
Yeah, Aaron, what's up?

399
00:26:20,629 --> 00:26:24,121
The Claudia Draper thing.
I'm gonna go ahead with it.

400
00:26:24,866 --> 00:26:26,026
Well, good, good.

401
00:26:26,101 --> 00:26:29,070
No, no. I'm gonna defend the girl
at a competency hearing.

402
00:26:29,137 --> 00:26:30,900
The judge set it up for Monday.

403
00:26:31,840 --> 00:26:35,332
Why are you doing that?
She's better off in a hospital than in prison.

404
00:26:35,410 --> 00:26:36,672
Don't mess this up.

405
00:26:36,845 --> 00:26:39,370
She wants to stand trial
on the manslaughter charge.

406
00:26:39,447 --> 00:26:40,846
I think she's up to it.

407
00:26:40,915 --> 00:26:43,110
- Oh, you do?
- Yeah, I do.

408
00:26:43,351 --> 00:26:47,515
I'll need the police reports
and a court order to enter the apartment.

409
00:26:48,089 --> 00:26:50,990
You're making a mistake. That girl is sick.

410
00:26:52,193 --> 00:26:56,129
I have an aunt who's crazier than she is.
She's president of the PTA.

411
00:26:56,731 --> 00:26:58,596
Arthur Kirk is very well-connected.

412
00:26:58,667 --> 00:27:02,364
He doesn't want his daughter going through
a trial. We're doing her a favor.

413
00:27:02,437 --> 00:27:06,931
The accused wants her day in court.
I still believe in that kind of stuff.

414
00:27:07,008 --> 00:27:08,600
Don't get high and mighty with me.

415
00:27:08,677 --> 00:27:11,441
Maybe you just don't have
a good enough case.

416
00:27:11,680 --> 00:27:14,080
Maybe you're trying to avoid a trial.

417
00:27:14,349 --> 00:27:16,579
I don't have a very good case? Really?

418
00:27:16,751 --> 00:27:20,016
She almost cut off a john's head.
You want her back on the streets?

419
00:27:20,155 --> 00:27:23,784
- Will your secretary pull the reports?
- She has more important things to do.

420
00:27:23,858 --> 00:27:24,847
Really?

421
00:27:25,393 --> 00:27:27,918
Then I'm gonna have to paper you
to death, Francis.

422
00:27:27,996 --> 00:27:31,432
You'll have to hire another secretary
just to keep up with the work.

423
00:27:32,667 --> 00:27:35,727
All right, kid.
But you're going up against me on this one.

424
00:27:38,907 --> 00:27:42,035
Hey, what are you doing?
Carla is waiting for Fantasy Island.

425
00:27:44,179 --> 00:27:46,977
Hey, fuck it.
Girlfriend, I want to watch my game show.

426
00:27:47,482 --> 00:27:50,781
That's not your card.
That's my card, Marian. I had four.

427
00:27:50,852 --> 00:27:53,218
One, two, three, four.

428
00:27:54,289 --> 00:27:55,517
Hey.

429
00:27:56,725 --> 00:27:58,352
I told you not to do that.

430
00:28:02,330 --> 00:28:05,925
- These aren't the same cards I had before.
- I don't want to see your cards.

431
00:28:06,534 --> 00:28:07,899
Come on, Suzanne.

432
00:28:09,170 --> 00:28:10,569
How many, Suzanne?

433
00:28:11,706 --> 00:28:13,674
- Three.
- No, five on that play.

434
00:28:13,742 --> 00:28:16,540
No, no. Wait. Stand pat, Suzanne.

435
00:28:16,611 --> 00:28:17,600
Stand pat?

436
00:28:17,679 --> 00:28:20,546
Yeah, you see, because you got
a good hand, so you can stay.

437
00:28:20,615 --> 00:28:23,914
Hey, hey, that's not fair. No, hey, look.

438
00:28:23,985 --> 00:28:26,749
Suzanne, you were gonna win.
Look, you got a full house.

439
00:28:26,821 --> 00:28:29,346
You got three jacks and two kings.

440
00:28:29,457 --> 00:28:32,585
Claudia? Claudia, would you like
to come into my office now?

441
00:28:34,229 --> 00:28:35,560
Would I like to?

442
00:28:37,599 --> 00:28:40,693
Let me put it this way.
Come into my office, Claudia.

443
00:28:49,844 --> 00:28:51,778
I see you're still taking notes.

444
00:28:53,148 --> 00:28:55,013
I have a feeling I'll need them.

445
00:28:55,450 --> 00:28:57,247
Need them for what, Claudia?

446
00:28:57,952 --> 00:29:01,718
Some guys are trying to put me away.

447
00:29:02,857 --> 00:29:05,849
When you say "some guys,"
who do you mean exactly?

448
00:29:06,795 --> 00:29:10,925
You mean, men in general,
or do you have some specific men in mind?

449
00:29:13,301 --> 00:29:15,428
- Claudia.
- What do you want?

450
00:29:15,837 --> 00:29:19,136
- I want to talk to you.
- I don't want to talk to you.

451
00:29:19,474 --> 00:29:22,307
Last time I talked to you,
you and Pancho Villa asked me...

452
00:29:22,377 --> 00:29:24,641
...stupid questions
and called me incompetent.

453
00:29:24,712 --> 00:29:28,045
- It would be better if you could trust me.
- Yeah? Why?

454
00:29:28,283 --> 00:29:30,717
Because you have so many degrees
on your wall?

455
00:29:33,888 --> 00:29:36,652
Do you think I'm one of the guys
trying to put you away?

456
00:29:36,724 --> 00:29:40,558
They don't pay you to turn me loose.
Do you guys work on commission?

457
00:29:44,799 --> 00:29:48,132
- Would you like a cup of coffee?
- Only if it has Thorazine in it.

458
00:29:48,269 --> 00:29:50,294
- Sorry, only milk and sugar.
- Pass.

459
00:29:51,973 --> 00:29:55,670
I heard you had quite a violent episode
in court yesterday.

460
00:29:57,011 --> 00:29:59,741
Where does it say I have to be nice
to get a fair trial?

461
00:30:01,382 --> 00:30:04,351
- You couldn't seem to control your anger.
- No, I couldn't.

462
00:30:04,619 --> 00:30:07,884
And based on the circumstances,
how did you expect me to act? Dead?

463
00:30:08,089 --> 00:30:11,354
- You're getting angry again.
- I've got a lot to be angry about.

464
00:30:13,728 --> 00:30:18,131
We all have these feelings, Claudia,
but we learn to control them.

465
00:30:19,734 --> 00:30:22,225
Well, don't you ever lose control, Herbie?

466
00:30:23,204 --> 00:30:25,104
Don't you ever let yourself go?

467
00:30:26,808 --> 00:30:29,038
You're a very frightened girl.

468
00:30:29,110 --> 00:30:32,045
And under stress,
you could become dangerous to others.

469
00:30:32,113 --> 00:30:33,171
Bullshit.

470
00:30:33,848 --> 00:30:36,214
That's what I plan to say in court
on Monday.

471
00:30:37,051 --> 00:30:39,986
You need treatment
in order to be able to control yourself.

472
00:30:40,922 --> 00:30:42,355
I'm in control.

473
00:30:43,291 --> 00:30:46,124
Because right now,
I'd like to wring your fucking neck...

474
00:30:47,061 --> 00:30:48,653
...but I'm not going to.

475
00:30:49,430 --> 00:30:51,796
Good. That's a step in the right direction.

476
00:30:53,001 --> 00:30:55,629
I'd like to help you
put your life back in order.

477
00:30:56,638 --> 00:30:59,607
