719
00:49:06,093 --> 00:49:07,185
Tell me...

720
00:49:07,294 --> 00:49:09,694
...you described the defendant
as dangerous.

721
00:49:10,230 --> 00:49:12,755
- Is that right?
- In my professional opinion.

722
00:49:13,333 --> 00:49:15,597
Did you ever see
the defendant hurt herself...

723
00:49:15,702 --> 00:49:17,033
...or anybody else?

724
00:49:17,838 --> 00:49:19,271
No, not personally.

725
00:49:19,339 --> 00:49:23,105
Ever hear her threaten to hurt herself
or anybody else?

726
00:49:23,410 --> 00:49:24,274
No.

727
00:49:25,512 --> 00:49:28,504
Did anybody at New York
County Prison Hospital...

728
00:49:28,582 --> 00:49:31,016
...ever see Claudia Draper hurt herself...

729
00:49:31,084 --> 00:49:33,848
...or anybody else,
or threaten to hurt herself...

730
00:49:34,421 --> 00:49:35,752
...or anybody else?

731
00:49:35,856 --> 00:49:37,221
Well, let me see.

732
00:49:40,961 --> 00:49:43,589
- Take your time, Doctor.
- Thank you.

733
00:49:47,501 --> 00:49:48,399
Yes.

734
00:49:49,002 --> 00:49:53,063
Three days after her arrival, she blackened
the eye of one of our other patients.

735
00:49:53,440 --> 00:49:54,964
She made a pass at me.

736
00:49:55,809 --> 00:49:58,209
The patient had to go to the infirmary.

737
00:50:00,280 --> 00:50:02,145
Your Honor, may I have a moment?

738
00:50:02,883 --> 00:50:03,872
Please.

739
00:50:07,721 --> 00:50:10,053
- Why didn't you tell me about this?
- I forgot.

740
00:50:10,123 --> 00:50:13,923
- I have to prove you're not dangerous.
- She grabbed my tit, I socked her.

741
00:50:13,994 --> 00:50:16,121
If you had tits, you'd do the same thing.

742
00:50:16,196 --> 00:50:17,254
I'm sorry.

743
00:50:17,464 --> 00:50:18,658
Mr. Levinsky?

744
00:50:20,400 --> 00:50:22,960
Are you prepared
to pursue a line of questioning?

745
00:50:23,036 --> 00:50:24,264
I...

746
00:50:25,138 --> 00:50:29,575
- I certainly hope so, Your Honor.
- I hope so, too. Continue.

747
00:50:33,413 --> 00:50:37,543
Dr. Morrison,
before your examination of Mrs. Draper...

748
00:50:37,617 --> 00:50:40,609
...were you aware
of why she had been arrested?

749
00:50:40,687 --> 00:50:42,848
Yes. First-degree manslaughter.

750
00:50:42,923 --> 00:50:45,619
It was more like womanslaughter,
but I finished first.

751
00:50:45,692 --> 00:50:47,159
That's enough, Mrs. Draper.

752
00:50:47,294 --> 00:50:52,061
Mr. Levinsky, you continue.
This time, stay on track.

753
00:50:54,568 --> 00:50:55,762
Dr. Morrison...

754
00:50:55,936 --> 00:50:58,700
...knowing that she had been arrested
for manslaughter...

755
00:50:58,772 --> 00:51:02,833
...were you in any way predisposed
to regard Mrs. Draper as dangerous?

756
00:51:05,178 --> 00:51:08,511
I considered that for a while,
but I held it in abeyance...

757
00:51:08,648 --> 00:51:12,516
...and let the examination provide me
with a proper psychiatric profile.

758
00:51:14,121 --> 00:51:16,453
You've been a psychiatrist for many years.

759
00:51:16,923 --> 00:51:18,185
That's correct.

760
00:51:19,826 --> 00:51:23,262
You must have testified
at many competency hearings, right?

761
00:51:23,864 --> 00:51:24,922
Hundreds.

762
00:51:25,699 --> 00:51:28,896
Do you have a standard set of questions
that you ask these patients?

763
00:51:28,969 --> 00:51:30,061
Yes, I do.

764
00:51:30,137 --> 00:51:32,537
So I imagine
you've already asked Mrs. Draper...

765
00:51:32,606 --> 00:51:34,938
...if she understood
the charges against her.

766
00:51:35,008 --> 00:51:36,270
That's correct.

767
00:51:36,910 --> 00:51:40,812
You asked her such questions as
what day of the week it was...

768
00:51:41,648 --> 00:51:44,811
...and what her parents' names were.
- Yes, that's right.

769
00:51:45,218 --> 00:51:47,413
Did she know the answers
to these questions?

770
00:51:47,487 --> 00:51:51,253
She refused to answer.
How could I know if she knew the answers?

771
00:51:51,391 --> 00:51:54,485
Let me ask the questions, okay?
I'm the attorney.

772
00:51:55,695 --> 00:51:56,787
Thank you.

773
00:51:57,597 --> 00:51:59,861
She could have known the answers.
Yes or no?

774
00:51:59,933 --> 00:52:01,833
Yes, she could have known the answers.

775
00:52:01,902 --> 00:52:05,861
You say she didn't answer you.
What did she do?

776
00:52:06,773 --> 00:52:07,933
She laughed.

777
00:52:08,708 --> 00:52:09,868
She laughed?

778
00:52:11,745 --> 00:52:14,475
- What else did she do?
- She never stopped taking notes.

779
00:52:14,548 --> 00:52:18,541
She was entirely belligerent in her attitude.
She wouldn't answer me.

780
00:52:18,618 --> 00:52:21,678
You're really not used to patients
who don't answer, are you?

781
00:52:21,755 --> 00:52:26,089
I'm used to all kinds. What concerns me is
their attitude and behavior.

782
00:52:26,193 --> 00:52:29,321
Could it be that the attitude
and behavior of this patient...

783
00:52:29,396 --> 00:52:32,024
...challenged you,
and got you a little bit hostile...

784
00:52:32,098 --> 00:52:34,658
...and perhaps colored the findings
in this report?

785
00:52:34,734 --> 00:52:39,228
I've been a psychiatrist for 30 years.
I know how to control my emotions.

786
00:52:39,639 --> 00:52:42,631
I did not show the patient
what I was feeling at the time.

787
00:52:42,709 --> 00:52:45,507
So you felt hostile, you just didn't show it.

788
00:52:45,679 --> 00:52:47,670
- I didn't say that.
- Yes, you did.

789
00:52:47,914 --> 00:52:51,907
- I didn't. Don't put words in my mouth.
- I'm not putting words in your mouth.

790
00:52:51,985 --> 00:52:54,283
I don't like your attitude, Mr. Levinsky!

791
00:52:54,821 --> 00:52:56,652
Getting a little hostile, Doctor?

792
00:52:56,723 --> 00:52:59,214
You're very clever
with your courtroom tricks.

793
00:52:59,559 --> 00:53:03,222
But what you're doing here
is depriving a sick girl of proper treatment.

794
00:53:03,763 --> 00:53:06,493
I'm a doctor.
I want her to receive that treatment.

795
00:53:06,600 --> 00:53:09,068
I don't care whether
you win this argument or not.

796
00:53:09,436 --> 00:53:11,870
The girl has a history,
and you're ignoring it.

797
00:53:11,938 --> 00:53:14,771
- A broken home, a broken marriage.
- Sounds like half of us.

798
00:53:14,841 --> 00:53:16,468
- Disillusion.
- That's the other half.

799
00:53:16,543 --> 00:53:19,410
Your Honor, could we eliminate
Mr. Levinsky's commentary...

800
00:53:19,479 --> 00:53:21,140
...and let the doctor speak?

801
00:53:22,582 --> 00:53:24,311
I agree. Go on, Doctor.

802
00:53:25,619 --> 00:53:29,555
We're not talking about a defendant,
we're talking about a very troubled girl.

803
00:53:29,623 --> 00:53:31,420
She's not a girl from the streets.

804
00:53:31,491 --> 00:53:34,756
She's a bright, upper-class girl
who couldn't cope, broke down!

805
00:53:35,528 --> 00:53:39,464
She's a girl with a history. Broke down!
She became a prostitute...

806
00:53:39,532 --> 00:53:42,262
...and in a homicidal rage,
killed one of her customers.

807
00:53:42,335 --> 00:53:44,963
I object. There's been no charge
of prostitution...

808
00:53:45,038 --> 00:53:47,165
...and any charge of homicide
has to be tried.

809
00:53:47,240 --> 00:53:49,333
We're talking about a breakdown.
When there's...

810
00:53:49,409 --> 00:53:50,433
Are you gonna allow this?

811
00:53:50,510 --> 00:53:51,499
My job's to put...

812
00:53:51,578 --> 00:53:54,206
The witness is making a speech.
It's not a proper forum.

813
00:53:54,281 --> 00:53:57,478
That can't be in a courtroom or prison.
It has to be in a hospital.

814
00:53:57,550 --> 00:53:58,949
Your Honor, I object!

815
00:53:59,019 --> 00:54:03,388
I would like everything about homicide
and prostitution stricken from the record.

816
00:54:04,691 --> 00:54:07,819
Mr. Levinsky, I am aware of the law.

817
00:54:07,894 --> 00:54:10,829
You're going to have to trust me
to separate the issues.

818
00:54:12,732 --> 00:54:14,165
I'm going to allow it.

819
00:54:18,571 --> 00:54:20,232
I have no more questions.

820
00:54:30,583 --> 00:54:33,882
With Your Honor's permission,
I will save my redirect for later.

821
00:54:36,156 --> 00:54:38,249
You may step down, Dr. Morrison.

822
00:54:41,094 --> 00:54:42,322
Thank you.

823
00:54:44,531 --> 00:54:46,556
I'd like to call Mrs. Arthur Kirk.

824
00:54:49,336 --> 00:54:52,499
- I don't want her up there.
- We don't make out the invitation list.

825
00:54:52,572 --> 00:54:54,472
I don't want to hear her!

826
00:54:56,476 --> 00:55:00,469
Your Honor,
I'd like to request a short recess.

827
00:55:00,814 --> 00:55:04,682
- I want to consult with my client.
- That's an excellent idea, Mr. Levinsky.

828
00:55:06,086 --> 00:55:08,520
We'll stand in recess for a few minutes.

829
00:55:08,788 --> 00:55:11,814
Please remain seated until the judge
leaves the courtroom.

830
00:55:13,126 --> 00:55:15,356
Go talk to her. Tell her you love her.

831
00:55:21,368 --> 00:55:22,562
Come with me.

832
00:55:32,212 --> 00:55:32,803
Claudia?

833
00:55:36,878 --> 00:55:40,109
Hello, darling. How are you?
You look thin.

834
00:55:44,486 --> 00:55:45,976
Are they feeding you?

835
00:55:47,422 --> 00:55:50,152
I can arrange to have food sent in.
Would you like that?

836
00:55:52,060 --> 00:55:53,425
You look tired.

837
00:55:54,196 --> 00:55:57,165
Are we making you tired?
You can say so, darling.

838
00:55:59,001 --> 00:56:00,730
Say something, please.

839
00:56:02,704 --> 00:56:04,137
Can we go in there?

840
00:56:04,339 --> 00:56:05,829
We can talk to her later.

841
00:56:05,907 --> 00:56:08,375
We'll talk later, Claudia.
We love you, darling.

842
00:56:11,613 --> 00:56:12,602
What?

843
00:56:13,649 --> 00:56:16,174
- We love you.
- Don't you know that?

844
00:56:17,252 --> 00:56:18,412
"We love you"?

845
00:56:19,054 --> 00:56:19,952
Yes!

846
00:56:23,091 --> 00:56:25,753
"We love you." One more time.

847
00:56:29,898 --> 00:56:30,865
"We... "

848
00:56:35,037 --> 00:56:36,061
Come on.

849
00:56:38,273 --> 00:56:39,205
"We... "

850
00:56:41,643 --> 00:56:42,575
We...

851
00:56:44,680 --> 00:56:45,612
"Love... "

852
00:56:46,815 --> 00:56:47,907
Love...

853
00:56:49,151 --> 00:56:50,140
"You."

854
00:56:50,919 --> 00:56:51,908
You.

855
00:56:57,626 --> 00:56:58,786
Outstanding.

856
00:57:00,262 --> 00:57:01,695
Let's go, Levinsky.

857
00:57:18,413 --> 00:57:21,871
- My wife and l...
- I don't want to hear about your wife.

858
00:57:26,254 --> 00:57:28,188
I'm sorry. Talk about your wife.

859
00:57:29,858 --> 00:57:32,224
I was thinking about
how people withhold...

860
00:57:34,129 --> 00:57:35,391
...in a family.

861
00:57:41,770 --> 00:57:43,465
How many kids do you have?

862
00:57:44,206 --> 00:57:45,935
Three. Two boys and a girl.

863
00:57:47,576 --> 00:57:49,271
You going to get divorced?

864
00:57:51,446 --> 00:57:53,175
We talk about it sometimes.

865
00:57:54,549 --> 00:57:56,210
Then we go to the movies.

866
00:57:58,954 --> 00:58:01,013
Why didn't you want her to testify?

867
00:58:02,524 --> 00:58:04,287
I just don't want her to testify.

868
00:58:04,359 --> 00:58:07,089
Why? You wouldn't let me
get an independent shrink.

869
00:58:07,696 --> 00:58:08,993
Officer?

870
00:58:09,731 --> 00:58:10,755
Harry?

871
00:58:11,466 --> 00:58:13,161
You can take me to my seat now.

872
00:58:13,435 --> 00:58:14,766
No gum, Claudia.

873
00:58:28,917 --> 00:58:31,909
And how soon after the divorce
did you marry Mr. Kirk?

874
00:58:32,387 --> 00:58:34,355
Eleven months. Nearly a year.

875
00:58:34,689 --> 00:58:39,353
- Did your daughter get along with Mr. Kirk?
- Fine. It was love at first sight for both.

876
00:58:42,664 --> 00:58:46,896
Can you tell us when you first noticed
any changes in her behavior?

877
00:58:49,171 --> 00:58:50,968
As early as the sixth grade.

878
00:58:51,406 --> 00:58:53,306
She was around 11.

879
00:58:55,277 --> 00:58:59,441
She'd always been active in school,
in sports and clubs and that sort of thing.

880
00:59:00,882 --> 00:59:03,407
She was always a very happy child.

881
00:59:03,985 --> 00:59:05,953
Then all of a sudden she withdrew.

882
00:59:06,688 --> 00:59:09,384
She seemed to live in a fantasy
most of the time.

883
00:59:09,791 --> 00:59:12,692
You never knew how she would act,
is that it?

884
00:59:13,261 --> 00:59:14,250
Never.

885
00:59:14,729 --> 00:59:17,960
One day she'd talk a blue streak
of utter nonsense.

886
00:59:18,400 --> 00:59:21,062
The next day, not a word. Later...

887
00:59:22,037 --> 00:59:25,871
...in high school, we had some problems...

888
00:59:26,374 --> 00:59:29,366
...with marijuana,
and staying out all night and...

889
00:59:30,145 --> 00:59:32,773
...there was a period of promiscuity.

890
00:59:34,683 --> 00:59:36,913
Once, she was 16...

891
00:59:37,152 --> 00:59:40,280
...we found her
at the mirror in the bathroom.

892
00:59:40,455 --> 00:59:43,049
She'd cut her hair an inch from her scalp.

893
00:59:43,391 --> 00:59:47,487
When we approached her,
she brandished the scissors on us.

894
00:59:47,662 --> 00:59:50,062
She turned the scissors on you
as if to attack you?

895
00:59:50,131 --> 00:59:52,827
Objection.
The prosecution is leading the witness.

896
00:59:52,934 --> 00:59:54,458
Sustained.

897
00:59:54,769 --> 00:59:56,862
Did you get any professional counseling?

898
00:59:57,639 --> 00:59:58,628
Arthur was against it.

899
00:59:58,707 --> 01:00:00,800
He doesn't believe
in airing family problems.

900
01:00:00,876 --> 01:00:05,370
And I agreed with him.
We assumed it was part of adolescence.

901
01:00:05,814 --> 01:00:08,840
Brandishing scissors on her parents,
a part of adolescence?

902
01:00:12,320 --> 01:00:14,845
Do you have any idea
what caused her behavior?

903
01:00:19,761 --> 01:00:22,628
I don't know. I don't know.

904
01:00:23,031 --> 01:00:26,558
I know that I made mistakes.

905
01:00:27,369 --> 01:00:32,238
Every mother makes mistakes,
and I'm sure that I made them sometimes.

906
01:00:33,842 --> 01:00:37,539
But not enough times for her
to carry on the way she did.

907
01:00:38,146 --> 01:00:41,912
Not enough times for her to drink and lie...

908
01:00:41,983 --> 01:00:44,383
...and cut school and not talk to me...

909
01:00:45,487 --> 01:00:50,117
...and not kiss me, not touch me.
Not enough times for that!

910
01:00:52,594 --> 01:00:53,788
I don't know.

911
01:00:54,796 --> 01:00:55,990
I don't know.

912
01:00:56,998 --> 01:00:58,727
When she was a little girl...

913
01:01:00,535 --> 01:01:02,162
...she loved me so much.

914
01:01:02,604 --> 01:01:06,734
She used to say, "I love you
to the moon and down again.

915
01:01:08,610 --> 01:01:10,805
"And around the world and back again."

916
01:01:11,579 --> 01:01:13,604
And I would answer, "I love you...

917
01:01:14,649 --> 01:01:18,551
"...to the sun and down again.

918
01:01:19,821 --> 01:01:23,120
"And around the stars and back again."

919
01:01:32,567 --> 01:01:34,228
Do you remember, Claudia?

920
01:01:37,472 --> 01:01:39,702
Just answer the questions, Mama.

921
01:01:41,343 --> 01:01:44,608
Did she get in touch with you
when her marriage failed?

922
01:01:45,413 --> 01:01:49,474
I found out from a friend.
So I called and said, "Is it true? "

923
01:01:49,751 --> 01:01:51,446
And she said, "Yes, it's true."

924
01:01:51,619 --> 01:01:53,678
There was a big silence. So I said:

925
01:01:53,855 --> 01:01:55,948
"Stay with us until you feel better."

926
01:01:56,458 --> 01:01:59,086
"No," she said. Just no.

927
01:02:01,129 --> 01:02:04,826
I was frightened for her.
A divorced woman is a target.

928
01:02:06,735 --> 01:02:09,465
She's easy prey to any polite man
who comes along.

929
01:02:09,971 --> 01:02:12,132
Were you able to keep in touch after that?

930
01:02:12,374 --> 01:02:14,001
I called. I called.

931
01:02:15,377 --> 01:02:17,277
But she never answered my messages.

932
01:02:17,746 --> 01:02:20,544
So instead of calling, I wrote.

933
01:02:22,650 --> 01:02:26,950
These are the letters. I have them here.
You should see them. You see...

934
01:02:27,022 --> 01:02:29,115
Your Honor, I never knew about this.

935
01:02:29,991 --> 01:02:32,152
Your Honor, I hardly think this is proper.

936
01:02:32,293 --> 01:02:33,123
Mrs. Kirk?

937
01:02:33,194 --> 01:02:37,324
Is this your handwriting?
Answer me! Is this your handwriting?

938
01:02:37,565 --> 01:02:38,691
Mrs. Kirk, please.

939
01:02:38,867 --> 01:02:41,461
I have 31 letters in my hand!

940
01:02:41,836 --> 01:02:44,862
And every one is marked
"Return to Sender"!

941
01:02:45,006 --> 01:02:46,530
I'm sorry, Your Honor.

942
01:02:51,279 --> 01:02:52,371
Poor Mama.

943
01:03:00,288 --> 01:03:01,380
Mrs. Kirk?

944
01:03:02,057 --> 01:03:04,184
- Are you all right?
- Mrs. Kirk?

945
01:03:04,993 --> 01:03:06,927
You could take a moment if you like.

946
01:03:07,262 --> 01:03:09,355
I'm all right. I'm sorry.

947
01:03:12,233 --> 01:03:15,293
I know this is difficult for you.
If you just bear with me.

948
01:03:16,204 --> 01:03:20,072
Your daughter has been
continuously withdrawing...

949
01:03:20,275 --> 01:03:22,709
...from you in the past 20 years,
is that right?

950
01:03:22,977 --> 01:03:24,342
Yes, that's true.

951
01:03:25,346 --> 01:03:27,541
Does your daughter need psychiatric help?

952
01:03:27,849 --> 01:03:31,615
Objection. Is Mrs. Kirk a medical expert?

953
01:03:31,953 --> 01:03:33,045
Sustained.

954
01:03:33,321 --> 01:03:37,223
Rephrase. As a parent, solely as a parent...

955
01:03:37,325 --> 01:03:41,125
...would you like to see your daughter
receive psychiatric treatment?

956
01:03:41,229 --> 01:03:42,253
Hey, I'm a grown-up.

957
01:03:42,330 --> 01:03:43,991
What difference does she make?

958
01:03:44,065 --> 01:03:46,158
- Miss Draper?
- It's my life, Stanley.

959
01:03:46,234 --> 01:03:47,531
You're trying my patience.

960
01:03:47,602 --> 01:03:50,594
Why do you listen to all this crap?
Why don't you listen to me?

961
01:03:50,672 --> 01:03:51,832
Sit down.

962
01:03:52,107 --> 01:03:54,507
You'll have a chance to testify later.

963
01:03:55,743 --> 01:03:57,108
Mrs. Kirk.

964
01:03:57,445 --> 01:03:58,503
I'm sorry.

965
01:03:58,780 --> 01:04:00,304
What was the question?

966
01:04:03,818 --> 01:04:06,810
"As a parent, solely,
would you like to see your daughter...

967
01:04:06,888 --> 01:04:09,220
"...receive psychiatric treatment? "

968
01:04:09,724 --> 01:04:10,986
She needs help.

969
01:04:11,926 --> 01:04:14,895
It's a difficult thing for a mother
to say about her daughter.

970
01:04:15,096 --> 01:04:16,154
Yes.

971
01:04:17,398 --> 01:04:18,797
She needs help.

972
01:04:19,033 --> 01:04:20,864
One last question, Mrs. Kirk.

973
01:04:21,035 --> 01:04:22,730
Do you love your daughter?

974
01:04:23,304 --> 01:04:25,169
Say it for the record, please.

975
01:04:30,178 --> 01:04:31,805
Yes.

976
01:04:32,514 --> 01:04:34,345
I love my daughter.

977
01:04:38,786 --> 01:04:41,016
Thank you. I have no further questions.

978
01:04:42,490 --> 01:04:45,254
- All true?
- Close enough. Let her go.

979
01:04:45,860 --> 01:04:48,226
Mr. Levinsky. Do you have any questions?

980
01:04:48,763 --> 01:04:50,822
Let her go, Levinsky.

981
01:04:52,233 --> 01:04:54,793
Would you like to take a minute?

982
01:04:55,737 --> 01:04:56,965
No, thank you.

983
01:04:57,906 --> 01:05:01,342
You stated that you
and the defendant's father...

984
01:05:10,418 --> 01:05:13,046
You testified that
when Claudia was in high school...

985
01:05:17,258 --> 01:05:18,247
What?

986
01:05:20,195 --> 01:05:22,459
You'll have to let me discredit the witness.

987
01:05:28,236 --> 01:05:29,703
Maybe you are crazy.

988
01:05:35,276 --> 01:05:37,244
I have no more questions, Your Honor.

989
01:05:39,480 --> 01:05:41,311
Mrs. Kirk, you may step down.

990
01:05:42,183 --> 01:05:44,344
I would like to call Mr. Arthur Kirk.

991
01:06:07,108 --> 01:06:08,541
Do you solemnly swear that...

992
01:06:08,610 --> 01:06:13,070
...your testimony shall be the truth,
the whole truth, and nothing but the truth?

993
01:06:13,314 --> 01:06:15,077
- I do.
- Be seated.

994
01:06:15,383 --> 01:06:16,611
Mr. MacMillan?

995
01:06:17,252 --> 01:06:20,585
How old was the defendant
when you married her mother?

996
01:06:21,089 --> 01:06:22,454
Claudia was 5.

997
01:06:23,258 --> 01:06:27,160
At that time, was there anything about her
that would have led you to believe...

998
01:06:27,262 --> 01:06:28,957
...that Claudia was troubled?

999
01:06:29,664 --> 01:06:33,498
She was frightened. They were both
frightened when I first met them.

1000
01:06:34,569 --> 01:06:37,663
They'd been abandoned, you see,
by Claudia's natural father.

1001
01:06:38,006 --> 01:06:41,134
So you would describe her
as frightened, traumatized?

1002
01:06:41,442 --> 01:06:44,309
Objection. The prosecution is
putting words in his mouth.

1003
01:06:44,512 --> 01:06:46,377
Overruled. Continue, Mr. Kirk.

1004
01:06:46,614 --> 01:06:47,478
Yes, sir.

1005
01:06:47,749 --> 01:06:50,309
She was always on guard, distrustful.

1006
01:06:51,286 --> 01:06:54,619
I shouldn't say always.
There were periods when she was happy.

1007
01:06:55,757 --> 01:06:57,190
But they were short-lived.

1008
01:06:57,592 --> 01:06:58,923
Did you get along well?

1009
01:06:58,993 --> 01:07:00,426
We got along fine.

1010
01:07:01,129 --> 01:07:02,426
I was her champion.

1011
01:07:02,563 --> 01:07:03,791
What do you mean?

1012
01:07:04,198 --> 01:07:05,460
Well...

1013
01:07:06,167 --> 01:07:07,896
...I forbade Rose to spank her.

1014
01:07:08,670 --> 01:07:12,333
Children should never be spanked.
It breaks their spirit.

1015
01:07:14,208 --> 01:07:18,144
- You tried to be a good father to her?
- Yes, I tried.

1016
01:07:19,113 --> 01:07:21,343
When I was courting her mother,
she said to me:

1017
01:07:21,416 --> 01:07:23,350
"Art, what about Claudia Faith? "

1018
01:07:23,951 --> 01:07:27,580
I didn't say, "Send her off to school,
get rid of her, send her away."

1019
01:07:27,755 --> 01:07:31,384
No, sir, I said,
"Rose, if you love her, I love her."

1020
01:07:32,427 --> 01:07:34,520
When she woke up
in the middle of the night...

1021
01:07:34,595 --> 01:07:37,860
...crying because of bad dreams,
I was the one who went to her.

1022
01:07:38,132 --> 01:07:40,760
I didn't know much about children,
but I learned.

1023
01:07:41,436 --> 01:07:44,303
And later, when she got a little older...

1024
01:07:45,340 --> 01:07:48,104
...I even took her to the office with me.

1025
01:07:48,176 --> 01:07:50,872
Given your years with her...

1026
01:07:51,279 --> 01:07:53,679
...and the close relationship
that you shared...

1027
01:07:53,881 --> 01:07:56,406
...would you say that you
understood her pretty well?

1028
01:07:56,484 --> 01:07:58,384
Objection. Leading the witness.

1029
01:07:59,854 --> 01:08:00,946
Overruled.

1030
01:08:02,423 --> 01:08:05,290
I understood her pretty well, yes,
I think so.

1031
01:08:08,062 --> 01:08:10,292
She was a troubled, but lovely, child.

1032
01:08:11,733 --> 01:08:14,031
A joy to be with, in spite of everything.

1033
01:08:15,403 --> 01:08:18,429
Even though I don't have the opportunity
to see her now...

1034
01:08:19,741 --> 01:08:21,971
...I’m sure she's a very special woman.

1035
01:08:23,478 --> 01:08:25,912
Were you surprised
when her marriage collapsed?

1036
01:08:26,080 --> 01:08:27,069
No.

1037
01:08:27,482 --> 01:08:30,576
All that surprised me was
that the marriage lasted that long.

1038
01:08:30,952 --> 01:08:33,113
I didn't know Peter until after the marriage.

1039
01:08:33,187 --> 01:08:34,586
I didn't know him well.

1040
01:08:34,722 --> 01:08:37,282
- He's a remarkable young man.
- You hated him.

1041
01:08:37,392 --> 01:08:39,587
Mrs. Draper, don't start up again.

1042
01:08:39,727 --> 01:08:42,594
That didn't mean anything
when he swore to tell the truth?

1043
01:08:42,797 --> 01:08:46,494
- He hated Peter's guts.
- You'll have an opportunity to speak later.

1044
01:08:47,702 --> 01:08:50,136
Speaking as a loving and devoted parent...

1045
01:08:50,338 --> 01:08:53,273
...do you believe
your stepdaughter needs hospitalization?

1046
01:08:54,075 --> 01:08:55,064
Yes.

1047
01:08:56,177 --> 01:08:57,576
I'm sorry to say I do.

1048
01:08:57,845 --> 01:08:58,834
Honey?

1049
01:09:00,615 --> 01:09:01,877
Go away, Peter.

1050
01:09:02,283 --> 01:09:04,251
Don't do this to me again.

1051
01:09:04,619 --> 01:09:07,952
I don't want to hurt you.
I promise, I'll just hold you.

1052
01:09:08,256 --> 01:09:11,020
Claudia? I love you.

1053
01:09:12,126 --> 01:09:13,525
Come on, open the door.

1054
01:09:14,929 --> 01:09:18,228
Mr. Kirk, did you hate Peter?

1055
01:09:18,566 --> 01:09:20,056
No, no, not at all.

1056
01:09:20,234 --> 01:09:22,498
I may have had
the typical father's reaction.

1057
01:09:22,603 --> 01:09:24,594
No man was good enough for my daughter.

1058
01:09:24,672 --> 01:09:26,264
- I see.
- Forget him.

1059
01:09:26,441 --> 01:09:30,673
You tied my hands pretty good.
Let me walk around a little bit, okay?

1060
01:09:32,413 --> 01:09:35,007
Mr. Kirk, do you have any idea
why Claudia attacked...

1061
01:09:35,082 --> 01:09:37,209
...her former attorney, Clarence Middleton?

1062
01:09:37,285 --> 01:09:39,185
Obviously, she didn't like his advice.

1063
01:09:39,253 --> 01:09:40,242
What was that advice?

1064
01:09:40,321 --> 01:09:45,224
I recall he suggested a hospital would be
a better place for her than Ryker's Island.

1065
01:09:46,127 --> 01:09:48,288
- Really?
- He felt it was the best way.

1066
01:09:48,863 --> 01:09:51,457
I see. "The best way."

1067
01:09:53,868 --> 01:09:55,335
The best way.

1068
01:09:56,771 --> 01:10:01,470
When you and Mrs. Kirk
talked to Dr. Morrison...

1069
01:10:01,576 --> 01:10:03,840
...when you chatted with him...

1070
01:10:04,045 --> 01:10:06,343
...about the crime
Claudia had been charged with...

1071
01:10:06,414 --> 01:10:08,644
...did he also indicate to you that...

1072
01:10:08,916 --> 01:10:10,781
...he thought it was the best way?

1073
01:10:11,352 --> 01:10:15,345
Mr. Levinsky, a trial is a public event.

1074
01:10:15,656 --> 01:10:18,523
If she were your daughter,
would you want her laughed at?

1075
01:10:18,793 --> 01:10:21,455
Hammered to a pulp by the attorneys
and the press?

1076
01:10:22,029 --> 01:10:25,328
She's just a client to you.
Day after tomorrow, you're gone.

1077
01:10:25,867 --> 01:10:27,892
But she's not just a client to me.

1078
01:10:28,336 --> 01:10:32,033
I'm not going to see her humiliated
in front of the whole world, no, sir.

1079
01:10:32,807 --> 01:10:35,401
No, this is not a common criminal.

1080
01:10:36,911 --> 01:10:38,708
My child is ill. She's sick.

1081
01:10:39,413 --> 01:10:42,905
And I will do everything I possibly can
to see that she gets better.

1082
01:10:43,050 --> 01:10:47,146
And that doesn't mean letting her sit here
in a public courtroom and be destroyed.

1083
01:10:59,033 --> 01:11:02,628
When you and Mrs. Kirk
were first married...

1084
01:11:18,519 --> 01:11:19,679
Strike that.

1085
01:11:21,923 --> 01:11:23,584
You're wasting your time.

1086
01:11:32,667 --> 01:11:35,636
Mr. Kirk, it's very clear to me
that both you and your wife...

1087
01:11:35,770 --> 01:11:39,536
...were very warm, loving parents.

1088
01:11:40,374 --> 01:11:42,899
- Both of you loved Claudia...
- And we still do.

1089
01:11:43,811 --> 01:11:45,574
That's right.

1090
01:11:45,846 --> 01:11:48,076
That's why I don't understand why...

1091
01:11:48,950 --> 01:11:51,316
...Claudia could behave
the way you described.

1092
01:11:51,786 --> 01:11:55,347
She was abandoned.
Her father walked out on her.

1093
01:11:55,790 --> 01:11:57,485
She was frightened, unprotected.

1094
01:11:57,692 --> 01:11:59,717
You replaced him
with something substantial.

1095
01:11:59,794 --> 01:12:02,262
Isn't that correct?
With love, affection and security.

1096
01:12:02,330 --> 01:12:03,319
All of those.

1097
01:12:03,397 --> 01:12:07,595
- Lf that's the case, it doesn't make sense.
- No, it certainly does not.

1098
01:12:12,940 --> 01:12:17,570
Maybe you gave her too much.
Maybe you were too generous.

1099
01:12:17,645 --> 01:12:20,512
I'm not ashamed to say I was generous.
I'm a generous man.

1100
01:12:20,581 --> 01:12:24,415
Well, is it possible then that you,
you spoiled her?

1101
01:12:25,152 --> 01:12:27,620
Look, I loved her.

1102
01:12:28,656 --> 01:12:31,022
And when you love someone,
you give them things.

1103
01:12:31,158 --> 01:12:33,649
Christmas, birthdays, graduation.

1104
01:12:34,595 --> 01:12:36,460
When she was young, I gave her presents.

1105
01:12:36,530 --> 01:12:39,727
When she got older, I gave her
gift certificates, sometimes cash.

1106
01:12:39,867 --> 01:12:41,926
- Cash?
- Yes.

1107
01:12:43,371 --> 01:12:47,102
Sorry. My mother always told me
it was wrong to give children money.

1108
01:12:47,942 --> 01:12:51,673
I'm afraid I disagree with your mother.
I'm a businessman.

1109
01:12:52,246 --> 01:12:54,476
To me, running a home is like
running a business.

1110
01:12:54,548 --> 01:12:58,040
You want someone to do something,
you give them an incentive to do it.

1111
01:12:58,552 --> 01:13:02,921
For instance, if she, let's say,
straightened out her room...

1112
01:13:03,057 --> 01:13:04,524
...she got $1.

1113
01:13:05,092 --> 01:13:08,220
If she came home from school
with a good report, she got $10.

1114
01:13:08,429 --> 01:13:10,021
- Like a reward.
- Exactly.

1115
01:13:10,131 --> 01:13:12,326
Let them have money,
give them a responsibility.

1116
01:13:12,400 --> 01:13:14,163
Let them make their own choices.

1117
01:13:14,368 --> 01:13:16,302
Now what did Claudia choose?

1118
01:13:16,470 --> 01:13:19,598
Mr. Kirk, isn't it true
that what Claudia did...

1119
01:13:19,774 --> 01:13:22,299
...was withdraw from you and Mrs. Kirk?

1120
01:13:22,510 --> 01:13:26,105
And from her husband Peter,
and from everyone else in her life.

1121
01:13:26,914 --> 01:13:29,712
God knows what's left
for her to withdraw from.

1122
01:13:41,862 --> 01:13:43,261
Speak no evil.

1123
01:13:44,865 --> 01:13:46,662
Speak no evil.

1124
01:13:46,834 --> 01:13:49,860
The people in your life have no mouths.
What can they talk about?

1125
01:13:49,937 --> 01:13:52,201
- Come on, Claudia, help me out.
- Stop it.

1126
01:13:53,340 --> 01:13:55,069
Mr. Levinsky?

1127
01:13:55,576 --> 01:13:57,476
Mr. Levinsky?

1128
01:13:59,947 --> 01:14:03,041
- Have you finished with the witness?
- Not quite yet, Your Honor.

1129
01:14:04,251 --> 01:14:07,880
You can bang that goddamn glass
all you want. I'm questioning this witness.

1130
01:14:12,093 --> 01:14:15,585
Boy, you must be a saint.
You really must be.

1131
01:14:15,730 --> 01:14:18,665
Only a saint could love
a frustrating woman like this.

1132
01:14:19,200 --> 01:14:22,499
- Do you really love a woman like this?
- I've always loved her.

1133
01:14:22,570 --> 01:14:25,095
How? How could you do that?

1134
01:14:25,573 --> 01:14:29,065
This is a woman even a father could hate,
one you could beat with a belt.

1135
01:14:29,310 --> 01:14:32,711
- Is this your idea of humor?
- This line of questioning is irrelevant.

1136
01:14:32,780 --> 01:14:35,112
- I'll allow it.
- Did you ever lose your temper?

1137
01:14:35,182 --> 01:14:38,845
- Sometimes, yes, I lost my temper.
- You did?

1138
01:14:39,053 --> 01:14:41,749
- I even spanked her.
- You did spank her!

1139
01:14:41,856 --> 01:14:45,087
I recall you told Mr. MacMillan
that you never spanked her.

1140
01:14:46,961 --> 01:14:51,421
Once or twice, if you call a smack
on the fanny a spank. Then I did.

1141
01:14:51,699 --> 01:14:54,361
And I probably did
a lot of other stupid things...

1142
01:14:54,535 --> 01:14:56,469
...but I was always there for her.

1143
01:14:56,570 --> 01:14:59,368
I helped her with her homework,
dressed her, bathed her.

1144
01:14:59,507 --> 01:15:02,032
I was the one
who gave her breakfast before school.

1145
01:15:02,109 --> 01:15:05,135
She never drove you crazy?
Come on, Mr. Kirk.

1146
01:15:05,212 --> 01:15:08,181
I know you're the perfect father,
but you never lost control?

1147
01:15:08,249 --> 01:15:09,238
Stop that.

1148
01:15:09,316 --> 01:15:13,116
- Didn't you ever want to beat her?
- Arthur would never hurt Claudia.

1149
01:15:13,254 --> 01:15:14,915
How would you know, Mama?

1150
01:15:19,894 --> 01:15:21,521
Mrs. Kirk, sit down, please.

1151
01:15:22,730 --> 01:15:25,665
Rose, sit down, darling, please.

1152
01:15:31,806 --> 01:15:33,000
Mr. Levinsky?

1153
01:15:43,951 --> 01:15:45,384
Mr. Levinsky?

1154
01:15:45,786 --> 01:15:47,117
Mr. Levinsky.

1155
01:15:50,825 --> 01:15:51,917
Excuse me.

1156
01:15:52,793 --> 01:15:54,226
Excuse me, Your Honor.

1157
01:15:56,330 --> 01:15:57,319
Proceed.

1158
01:16:01,669 --> 01:16:02,658
Mr. Kirk...

1159
01:16:05,039 --> 01:16:08,304
...you said that among
the many fatherly duties...

1160
01:16:08,442 --> 01:16:12,208
...that you assumed
when Claudia entered your life was...

1161
01:16:13,848 --> 01:16:16,282
...bathing her.
Do you remember saying that?

1162
01:16:17,151 --> 01:16:19,142
- Please respond verbally.
- Yes, I did.

1163
01:16:19,286 --> 01:16:22,483
How long did you practice
this particular fatherly duty?

1164
01:16:22,990 --> 01:16:24,514
Objection, Your Honor!

1165
01:16:25,359 --> 01:16:27,691
Overruled. Answer the question, Mr. Kirk.

1166
01:16:30,531 --> 01:16:32,123
I don't remember.

1167
01:16:34,935 --> 01:16:36,800
Did it stop when she was 5?

1168
01:16:38,305 --> 01:16:40,432
Did it go on a year and stop
when she was 6?

1169
01:16:40,507 --> 01:16:41,599
What are you suggesting?

1170
01:16:41,675 --> 01:16:45,167
Did it stop in two years when she was 7?
I remind you you're under oath.

1171
01:16:45,512 --> 01:16:47,104
I don't know. Not long.

1172
01:16:47,448 --> 01:16:49,211
- She liked me to do it.
- Do what?

1173
01:16:49,283 --> 01:16:51,080
- To bathe her.
- To bathe her?

1174
01:16:53,354 --> 01:16:54,548
To bathe her.

1175
01:16:55,456 --> 01:16:56,718
It was nothing!

1176
01:16:57,157 --> 01:16:58,818
I object to your insinuations!

1177
01:16:59,126 --> 01:17:01,890
My daughter locked me out
of the bathroom when she was 4.

1178
01:17:02,062 --> 01:17:04,053
- How old was Claudia?
- Claudia, please.

1179
01:17:04,198 --> 01:17:06,632
How old was she? 10? 12?

1180
01:17:06,934 --> 01:17:08,299
How old were you?

1181
01:17:08,903 --> 01:17:10,063
How old was she?

1182
01:17:10,337 --> 01:17:14,000
Was she 13 when you stopped bathing her?
Was she 14?

1183
01:17:14,108 --> 01:17:16,042
- She was a child...
- How old?

1184
01:17:18,712 --> 01:17:22,375
- He's harassing the witness.
- I'd like to hear an answer.

1185
01:17:22,449 --> 01:17:24,815
- How old?
- I don't remember.

1186
01:17:24,952 --> 01:17:26,385
I was 16.

1187
01:17:48,642 --> 01:17:52,601
What else occurred in that bathroom
between you and your stepdaughter?

1188
01:17:55,015 --> 01:17:56,505
What occurred in her bedroom?

1189
01:17:56,583 --> 01:17:58,983
Stop it! Stop it!

1190
01:17:59,320 --> 01:18:02,653
It's not true, Rose, you know it's not true.

1191
01:18:02,723 --> 01:18:04,987
Did you make her your lover?

1192
01:18:05,125 --> 01:18:07,719
- I told you, it was nothing.
- How old was she, Mr. Kirk?

1193
01:18:07,795 --> 01:18:09,626
That's enough, Mr. Levinsky.

1194
01:18:09,830 --> 01:18:10,990
When did it begin?

1195
01:18:11,065 --> 01:18:14,000
You little bastard! Look what you've done.

1196
01:18:14,068 --> 01:18:16,400
Didn't you make
your stepdaughter your lover?

1197
01:18:16,837 --> 01:18:18,634
That's enough, Mr. Levinsky.

1198
01:18:18,739 --> 01:18:20,366
Tell them it's a mistake.

1199
01:18:20,674 --> 01:18:22,073
I didn't do anything wrong.

1200
01:18:22,142 --> 01:18:23,803
Calm yourself.

1201
01:18:24,111 --> 01:18:25,635
Claudia, believe me, it's not true.

1202
01:18:25,713 --> 01:18:27,010
Mr. Kirk, sit down!

1203
01:18:27,348 --> 01:18:29,316
- Claudia?
- No, Daddy.

1204
01:18:29,450 --> 01:18:31,441
- Claudia, please.
- You stop that!

1205
01:18:31,518 --> 01:18:33,008
Tell him it's not true.

1206
01:18:33,153 --> 01:18:34,745
Mr. Kirk, control yourself.

1207
01:18:36,323 --> 01:18:38,086
Mr. Kirk, you're out of order.

1208
01:18:38,158 --> 01:18:39,819
No, please. Don't let him touch me.

1209
01:18:39,893 --> 01:18:42,293
- She's not in her right mind.
- That's enough!

1210
01:18:42,363 --> 01:18:44,627
I love you, baby.
Tell Daddy what you want.

1211
01:18:45,065 --> 01:18:49,058
I'll give it to you. Please!
I'm pleading with you!

1212
01:18:49,336 --> 01:18:52,601
Don't let him touch me.
Don't let him hurt me anymore.

1213
01:19:45,059 --> 01:19:45,923
It's me.

1214
01:19:48,295 --> 01:19:49,284
Aaron.

1215
01:19:56,136 --> 01:19:57,103
Aaron?

1216
01:20:00,974 --> 01:20:01,963
I'm sorry.

1217
01:20:05,245 --> 01:20:07,770
I got so wrapped up
in being a goddamn lawyer.

1218
01:20:13,320 --> 01:20:14,480
Did we lose?

1219
01:20:17,291 --> 01:20:18,315
Not yet.

1220
01:20:20,461 --> 01:20:21,826
Maybe they're right.

1221
01:20:26,366 --> 01:20:27,594
Maybe I am crazy.

1222
01:20:36,643 --> 01:20:38,372
I didn't tell him to stop!

1223
01:20:40,047 --> 01:20:41,742
I didn't tell him to stop.

1224
01:20:44,017 --> 01:20:45,609
You were a little girl.

1225
01:20:47,855 --> 01:20:50,653
I wanted him to love me, that's all.

1226
01:20:51,892 --> 01:20:53,985
Claudia, that's what everybody wants.

1227
01:20:55,696 --> 01:20:57,687
Oh, I'm afraid.

1228
01:20:59,399 --> 01:21:00,889
I'm afraid, I can't go back.

1229
01:21:02,136 --> 01:21:03,967
I'll go crazy in there again.

1230
01:21:07,741 --> 01:21:09,072
Don't be afraid.

1231
01:21:11,345 --> 01:21:12,505
You're sane.

1232
01:21:14,081 --> 01:21:15,412
Do you hear me?

1233
01:21:24,324 --> 01:21:28,124
You got to go home on the subway.

1234
01:21:30,998 --> 01:21:31,930
What?

1235
01:21:34,201 --> 01:21:36,396
You're supposed to be with the missus.

1236
01:21:41,441 --> 01:21:42,135
No.

1237
01:21:44,545 --> 01:21:46,911
No, I'm supposed to be right here.

1238
01:22:12,105 --> 01:22:13,231
Get up.

1239
01:22:14,374 --> 01:22:16,103
- What?
- Get up. We have to talk.

1240
01:22:16,710 --> 01:22:17,608
I'm eating.

1241
01:22:18,579 --> 01:22:19,568
You finished.

1242
01:22:20,113 --> 01:22:22,479
- You got a problem?
- You drugged my client.

1243
01:22:22,916 --> 01:22:26,215
After what you put her through,
I had to give her some sedation.

1244
01:22:26,453 --> 01:22:29,547
- I want her lucid. Not drugged.
- She'll be fine tomorrow.

1245
01:22:29,790 --> 01:22:32,384
If she's a zombie tomorrow,
I'll sue your ass.

1246
01:22:33,093 --> 01:22:35,493
Don't threaten me,
you lawyer son of a bitch!

1247
01:22:38,365 --> 01:22:39,832
Bon appetit.

1248
01:22:55,749 --> 01:22:57,683
You don't have to do this today.

1249
01:22:58,418 --> 01:22:59,476
I'm okay.

1250
01:23:03,590 --> 01:23:05,820
Mr. Levinsky, are you ready to proceed?

1251
01:23:06,560 --> 01:23:07,652
Yes, I am.

1252
01:23:08,195 --> 01:23:10,322
I call the defendant, Claudia Faith Draper.

1253
01:23:10,397 --> 01:23:14,834
Mrs. Draper, you may testify
from your seat, if you like.

1254
01:23:15,969 --> 01:23:16,867
Why?

1255
01:23:17,504 --> 01:23:19,631
I thought you might be more comfortable.

1256
01:23:22,175 --> 01:23:24,302
I'd rather go on the stand.

1257
01:23:24,478 --> 01:23:27,914
I have no objection to your being
sworn in right there.

1258
01:23:27,981 --> 01:23:30,279
I'm not an invalid, I'm a witness, right?

1259
01:23:30,384 --> 01:23:32,716
Witnesses go in the box.
So, if you don't mind...

1260
01:23:32,786 --> 01:23:34,720
- As you like.
- Thank you.

1261
01:23:37,758 --> 01:23:39,623
I'm not gonna hurt you. Relax.

1262
01:23:45,465 --> 01:23:47,660
Left hand on the Bible, raise your right.

1263
01:23:48,135 --> 01:23:52,128
Do you swear the testimony you shall give
shall be the truth...

1264
01:23:52,205 --> 01:23:54,173
...the whole truth
and nothing but the truth?

1265
01:23:54,241 --> 01:23:56,607
- I certainly do.
- Please be seated.

1266
01:24:03,016 --> 01:24:04,074
Are you okay?

1267
01:24:08,221 --> 01:24:09,381
Mrs. Draper...

1268
01:24:12,292 --> 01:24:14,487
You understand
the charge made against you?

1269
01:24:16,930 --> 01:24:19,330
- The manslaughter charge, right?
- Yes.

1270
01:24:20,267 --> 01:24:21,734
Could you define it for me?

1271
01:24:26,073 --> 01:24:30,009
First-degree manslaughter
is a Class B felony...

1272
01:24:32,045 --> 01:24:33,171
...under...

1273
01:24:42,422 --> 01:24:46,153
...2.5 point something
of the Penal Law Code?

1274
01:24:48,028 --> 01:24:49,256
I forgot...

1275
01:24:49,396 --> 01:24:52,490
Have you been given any medication
in the last 24 hours?

1276
01:24:52,566 --> 01:24:55,501
- Tranquilizers, sedatives?
- Yes, I told him I didn't need them.

1277
01:24:55,569 --> 01:24:57,002
Objection, Your Honor.

1278
01:24:57,070 --> 01:24:59,937
If he wants medical testimony,
he can question Dr. Morrison.

1279
01:25:00,040 --> 01:25:01,098
Sustained.

1280
01:25:01,174 --> 01:25:05,873
Tell me your understanding
of the legal concept...

1281
01:25:06,246 --> 01:25:07,907
...of justifiable force?

1282
01:25:13,920 --> 01:25:16,855
That's when someone's beating
your brains out and...

1283
01:25:16,957 --> 01:25:18,788
...you can stop them any way you can.

1284
01:25:18,859 --> 01:25:19,985
Thank you.

1285
01:25:20,927 --> 01:25:24,385
Would you tell us your understanding...

1286
01:25:25,232 --> 01:25:28,224
...of the provisions of the 730 process?

1287
01:25:29,503 --> 01:25:30,470
Yeah.

1288
01:25:32,806 --> 01:25:36,799
If I lose today,
they can commit me for a year.

1289
01:25:38,512 --> 01:25:43,074
Sixty days before the year is up,
the hospital can ask to retain me.

1290
01:25:45,285 --> 01:25:46,616
If I lose again...

1291
01:25:48,121 --> 01:25:50,021
...I’m gone for another year.

1292
01:25:50,424 --> 01:25:54,724
From then on,
it's two-thirds of the maximum sentence...

1293
01:25:55,462 --> 01:25:57,089
...which comes out to be...

1294
01:25:57,330 --> 01:25:59,764
...sixteen or 17 years without a trial.

1295
01:26:00,100 --> 01:26:01,067
Your Honor...

1296
01:26:01,201 --> 01:26:04,762
Mr. MacMillan, you'll have ample time
to cross-exam. Let her finish.

1297
01:26:06,339 --> 01:26:07,431
Mrs. Draper...

1298
01:26:08,842 --> 01:26:11,106
...what does all that mean to you?

1299
01:26:11,545 --> 01:26:14,139
It means if they do it right,
they can lock me up...

1300
01:26:14,314 --> 01:26:16,339
...in a mental hospital forever.

1301
01:26:16,550 --> 01:26:18,916
- The witness is exaggerating.
- No, I'm not.

1302
01:26:19,085 --> 01:26:22,452
There's a book on the table,
called Criminal Law of New York.

1303
01:26:23,356 --> 01:26:24,050
Look it up.

1304
01:26:24,124 --> 01:26:27,116
The witness is extending
the practical limits of the statute.

1305
01:26:27,227 --> 01:26:29,161
I didn't write the book.

1306
01:26:29,696 --> 01:26:32,961
The Honorable Eugene R. Canudo...

1307
01:26:33,099 --> 01:26:35,693
...Judge, New York City Criminal Court,
he wrote it.

1308
01:26:37,370 --> 01:26:41,568
However it's executed, that is the statute,
as you should know.

1309
01:26:43,777 --> 01:26:45,301
Proceed, Mr. Levinsky.

1310
01:26:50,517 --> 01:26:53,384
Can you tell us the names of the doctors
who examined you?

1311
01:26:54,020 --> 01:26:55,180
Yes, I can.

1312
01:26:56,022 --> 01:26:59,321
Julio Arantes and Herbert Morrison.
Herbert A. Morrison.

1313
01:26:59,693 --> 01:27:03,254
And how long was
Dr. Arantes' examination?

1314
01:27:04,364 --> 01:27:06,889
Fifteen, maybe 20 minutes.
He barely speaks English.

1315
01:27:07,133 --> 01:27:08,100
Objection.

1316
01:27:08,201 --> 01:27:10,692
He doesn't.
His Spanish isn't so hot, either.

1317
01:27:12,305 --> 01:27:14,603
How long was Dr. Morrison's examination?

1318
01:27:16,443 --> 01:27:19,071
Fifty, fifty-five minutes.
He knows more English.

1319
01:27:22,849 --> 01:27:25,875
Tell me, do you accept the findings
of these examinations...

1320
01:27:26,052 --> 01:27:27,917
...given to you at the hospital?

1321
01:27:27,988 --> 01:27:29,046
I do not.

1322
01:27:29,789 --> 01:27:32,724
Do you believe you are mentally prepared
to go to trial?

1323
01:27:33,026 --> 01:27:34,118
Yes, I do.

1324
01:27:35,629 --> 01:27:36,721
Thank you.

1325
01:27:38,999 --> 01:27:40,557
I have no more questions.

1326
01:27:41,668 --> 01:27:42,896
Mr. MacMillan?

1327
01:27:47,407 --> 01:27:50,137
- Claudia, if you're tired...
- I'm not tired.

1328
01:27:50,944 --> 01:27:53,071
And I'd like you to call me Mrs. Draper.

1329
01:27:53,880 --> 01:27:54,904
Very well.

1330
01:27:55,382 --> 01:27:57,111
When I get tired I'll let you know.

1331
01:27:57,183 --> 01:27:58,445
Mrs. Draper...

1332
01:27:58,552 --> 01:27:59,780
Are you tired?

1333
01:28:01,821 --> 01:28:03,516
How long were you married?

1334
01:28:05,725 --> 01:28:07,886
Six weeks short of 10 years.

1335
01:28:08,461 --> 01:28:10,156
Was this a happy marriage?

1336
01:28:10,730 --> 01:28:11,662
It had its moments.

1337
01:28:11,731 --> 01:28:14,131
- Do you have children from this marriage?
- No.

1338
01:28:14,334 --> 01:28:15,699
Was that by choice?

1339
01:28:16,236 --> 01:28:17,225
Yes.

1340
01:28:17,304 --> 01:28:18,498
Whose choice?

1341
01:28:19,439 --> 01:28:20,428
We agreed.

1342
01:28:20,607 --> 01:28:22,040
You jointly agreed?

1343
01:28:23,176 --> 01:28:27,272
Yes. I told him if I got pregnant,
I'd leave him. So he agreed.

1344
01:28:27,681 --> 01:28:30,172
- And you didn't get pregnant?
- No, I did.

1345
01:28:30,250 --> 01:28:32,115
- You did get pregnant?
- Yes, I did.

1346
01:28:32,252 --> 01:28:35,779
We came home late from a party one night
and we were a little drunk.

1347
01:28:35,956 --> 01:28:39,289
I put too much jelly
on my diaphragm and...

1348
01:28:40,627 --> 01:28:43,255
Did your husband leave you
when you got pregnant?

1349
01:28:45,765 --> 01:28:47,289
No, I had an abortion.

1350
01:28:47,867 --> 01:28:48,765
Why?

1351
01:28:51,938 --> 01:28:53,769
I don't believe in childhood.

1352
01:29:03,516 --> 01:29:05,211
Did you love your husband?

1353
01:29:07,387 --> 01:29:08,581
I don't know.

1354
01:29:10,323 --> 01:29:12,814
Where did you move
when your marriage collapsed?

1355
01:29:13,293 --> 01:29:14,760
I guess I loved him.

1356
01:29:15,629 --> 01:29:16,618
What?

1357
01:29:17,097 --> 01:29:18,530
Where did you move?

1358
01:29:19,599 --> 01:29:20,998
501 East 66th Street.

1359
01:29:21,101 --> 01:29:23,433
- You lived there at the time of your arrest?
- Yeah.

1360
01:29:23,503 --> 01:29:26,529
- What is the rent at that address?
- $2,400 a month.

1361
01:29:26,640 --> 01:29:28,870
When you moved in,
what was your income?

1362
01:29:31,745 --> 01:29:35,647
Peter gave me $10,000 when I signed
the separation agreement.

1363
01:29:35,715 --> 01:29:37,342
Did you ask your parents for money?

1364
01:29:38,084 --> 01:29:38,880
No.

1365
01:29:38,952 --> 01:29:43,116
Could Mr. MacMillan tell us why he is
so fascinated with Mrs. Draper's finances?

1366
01:29:43,256 --> 01:29:45,486
Does he plan to sell her a car?

1367
01:29:47,360 --> 01:29:48,884
Where are you heading?

1368
01:29:49,229 --> 01:29:52,721
My next group of questions will show,
Your Honor, if you'll indulge me.

1369
01:29:52,932 --> 01:29:53,956
Proceed.

1370
01:29:54,701 --> 01:29:58,102
So you lived off the $10,000
your husband gave you?

1371
01:29:58,772 --> 01:30:01,366
No, I spent that on furniture
and kitchen stuff.

1372
01:30:02,442 --> 01:30:03,966
What did you live on?

1373
01:30:07,847 --> 01:30:09,678
- Gifts.
- Gifts.

1374
01:30:12,085 --> 01:30:13,677
Gifts from whom?

1375
01:30:15,855 --> 01:30:17,345
- Friends.
- Men friends?

1376
01:30:21,127 --> 01:30:24,255
And what did these men friends give you?
Jewelry?

1377
01:30:25,598 --> 01:30:26,428
Sometimes.

1378
01:30:26,566 --> 01:30:27,498
Furs?

1379
01:30:29,302 --> 01:30:30,929
I got a fox boa once.

1380
01:30:32,305 --> 01:30:34,432
- Did they give you food?
- Food?

1381
01:30:35,642 --> 01:30:38,133
One guy used to bring caviar.
Is that what you mean?

1382
01:30:38,478 --> 01:30:41,914
Did you exchange your jewels and furs
for food at the market?

1383
01:30:42,082 --> 01:30:44,016
- Isn't that silly?
- Did you?

1384
01:30:44,150 --> 01:30:45,014
No.

1385
01:30:45,452 --> 01:30:48,444
- I assume you didn't live on caviar.
- Hardly.

1386
01:30:48,755 --> 01:30:51,280
Did you use those gifts to pay your rent?

1387
01:30:54,627 --> 01:30:55,719
Excuse me.

1388
01:30:56,262 --> 01:30:58,162
Is it legal to take cash gifts?

1389
01:30:59,032 --> 01:31:00,431
I beg your pardon?

1390
01:31:01,000 --> 01:31:05,437
I mean, if I say to you, "Stanley,
here's $500 just because I like you... "

1391
01:31:05,638 --> 01:31:06,866
...is that legal?

1392
01:31:07,974 --> 01:31:09,373
Yes, that's legal.

1393
01:31:09,509 --> 01:31:11,636
Thank you. A lot of the gifts were cash.

1394
01:31:11,845 --> 01:31:15,110
And these cash gifts were enough
to pay your expenses?

1395
01:31:17,016 --> 01:31:19,849
What did these men expect in exchange
for the cash gifts?

1396
01:31:20,086 --> 01:31:23,852
- Is counsel leading up to...
- Your Honor, I haven't used the word "fee."

1397
01:31:24,390 --> 01:31:25,914
I'll permit an answer.

1398
01:31:26,559 --> 01:31:30,586
What did these men friends expect
in return for these cash gifts?

1399
01:31:32,732 --> 01:31:33,858
Friendship.

1400
01:31:35,301 --> 01:31:37,735
"Friendship." What kind of friendship?

1401
01:31:37,804 --> 01:31:39,999
Objection! The question is vague
and misleading.

1402
01:31:40,073 --> 01:31:41,165
Overruled.

1403
01:31:41,508 --> 01:31:45,467
These men that gave you cash gifts,
did they expect you to talk to them?

1404
01:31:46,279 --> 01:31:48,076
- Did you listen to them?
- God, yes.

1405
01:31:48,181 --> 01:31:50,274
- And you did them favors?
- Your Honor.

1406
01:31:50,450 --> 01:31:53,214
You did them favors. What kind?

1407
01:31:53,353 --> 01:31:54,945
Objection on the same grounds.

1408
01:31:55,021 --> 01:31:57,990
What kind of favors did you do
in exchange for these gifts?

1409
01:31:58,258 --> 01:32:00,988
What does it matter how Mrs. Draper
makes her living?

1410
01:32:01,060 --> 01:32:03,654
What kind of favors?

1411
01:32:03,797 --> 01:32:06,288
Let's stop all the bullshit
and get to the point.

1412
01:32:06,766 --> 01:32:09,360
You want to know what I do for a living?
Ask me.

1413
01:32:10,603 --> 01:32:14,039
My time is very expensive, Mr. MacMillan.
Probably more than yours.

1414
01:32:15,208 --> 01:32:18,143
I get $500 an hour. How much do you get?

1415
01:32:19,078 --> 01:32:23,708
I get $400 for a straight lay,
$300 for a hand job and $500 for head.

1416
01:32:24,984 --> 01:32:27,509
If you wanna wear my panties,
that's another $100.

1417
01:32:27,821 --> 01:32:30,847
You take them home, Mr. MacMillan,
that's another $100.

1418
01:32:31,224 --> 01:32:34,125
No whips, no ropes, no spikes.
I've got liquor and grass.

1419
01:32:34,194 --> 01:32:37,061
Anything else, you bring your own.
It works like this.

1420
01:32:39,165 --> 01:32:41,065
You call me up, we make a date.

1421
01:32:42,402 --> 01:32:45,803
I look you over. And if I like you...

1422
01:32:47,407 --> 01:32:48,772
...we make a deal.

1423
01:32:49,442 --> 01:32:51,603
And, darling, I am worth the trouble.

1424
01:32:52,545 --> 01:32:55,036
Take my word for it, if you want the best.

1425
01:32:56,816 --> 01:32:58,909
Do you want the best, Mr. MacMillan?

1426
01:33:00,520 --> 01:33:03,819
I am talking about
taking your body to heaven...

1427
01:33:04,924 --> 01:33:07,950
...and sending your mind south.

1428
01:33:08,695 --> 01:33:11,186
I'm talking about spoiling you so bad...

1429
01:33:11,931 --> 01:33:14,229
...you'll hate every other woman you touch.

1430
01:33:16,269 --> 01:33:18,737
I'm talking about my mouth
on your mouth...

1431
01:33:19,239 --> 01:33:20,501
...and my tongue...

1432
01:33:22,141 --> 01:33:24,075
...anywhere you want it.

1433
01:33:26,846 --> 01:33:29,747
I'm talking about indulging
your every fantasy...

1434
01:33:31,417 --> 01:33:34,147
...and then giving you those fantasies
one by one.

1435
01:33:35,555 --> 01:33:39,457
Just for you. All for you. Nobody but you.

1436
01:33:42,962 --> 01:33:44,793
Do you get all that, darling?

1437
01:33:46,833 --> 01:33:48,391
Would you like that, baby?

1438
01:33:49,669 --> 01:33:51,660
Do you get what I'm telling you?

1439
01:33:54,307 --> 01:33:57,276
Do you all get what I'm telling you?

1440
01:34:08,821 --> 01:34:10,721
Now, could he bust me for that?

1441
01:34:13,192 --> 01:34:14,682
Can he...

1442
01:34:17,263 --> 01:34:18,890
No, he can't bust you.

1443
01:34:19,465 --> 01:34:20,397
Good.

1444
01:34:25,638 --> 01:34:29,335
- That's very enlightening.
- I thought you'd like it.

1445
01:34:30,843 --> 01:34:34,472
How long did you perform these favors?

1446
01:34:35,281 --> 01:34:37,215
35 months, 24 days.

1447
01:34:38,851 --> 01:34:40,842
Why did you perform these favors?

1448
01:34:42,388 --> 01:34:44,049
For $100,000 a year, net.

1449
01:34:45,558 --> 01:34:47,685
Did you ever ask your parents for money?

1450
01:34:49,329 --> 01:34:50,193
No.

1451
01:34:50,330 --> 01:34:53,094
Do you believe they would have refused
to give it to you?

